title: ma's salmon salad
directions: Add and mix into vegetable ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars and milk in heavy buttered saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan (thick).

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: mound candy bars
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: beef 'n' noodle jackpot
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain fat.
Add soup, water and noodles; blend well.
Cover and bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and pepper and 1/2 cheese.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make cream sauce with butter, flour, milk and asparagus juice. Add grated cheese.
Season with salt and Tabasco.
Alternate layers of asparagus, sliced eggs, pimento and sauce.
Again layer. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: almond chicken fingers
directions: Lightly salt and flour chicken fingers.
Saute them in butter in a large pan until the chicken turns white.
Warm the liqueur and flame it over the chicken.
Add the chicken bouillon, garlic powder, pepper, mushrooms and bring to a boil.
Cook over moderate heat until liquid is reduced to half the original amount.
Add heavy cream; heat through but do not boil.
Check seasoning. Serve over rice, garnished with parsley.
Must serve immediately.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 inch square pan.
In layers, add canned fruit.
Mix together flour, sugar, and milk.
Pour over canned fruit and bake on 425 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Mix milk and oil well.
Pour in flour.
Mix until flour is damp.
Shape in pie pan.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese with boiling water.
Prepare pie filling according to directions, except add cheese mixture for cold water. Pour immediately into a baked graham cracker crust and top with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, layer peppers. Spread cheese. Beat eggs and spread on top. Heat at 350° until hot. Serve warm with crackers.

title: quick and easy broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add other ingredients and cook in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Use electric mixer to mix; chill first if possible.
Pour in 4-quart freezer, then add sweet milk, if not full, to line in freezer.
Stir, then ready to freeze.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cube bread in a 13-inch glass baking pan, greased.
Then layer sausage, then cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over sausage mixture.
Mix soup with milk and pour over mixture.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° or until light brown and bubbly.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until done.
Add soup, green beans and corn; heat to boil.
Cover over with mashed potatoes.
You can eat as is or brown potatoes in oven (350°).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: never fail pralines
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, granulated sugar, milk and Karo. Boil this mixture until it forms a soft ball dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until creamy and drop by tablespoons onto wax paper or Tupperware sheet.
Makes 24 to 30 large pieces.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in small shallow bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar and shake vigorously.
Pour over asparagus. Cover and chill at least four hours.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done (cube).
Stir chicken, soup, chilies and cheese together.
Saute in butter, celery and onion.
Add altogether and place in casserole dish.
Top with croutons or snack crackers.
Cover with melted margarine.
Place in preheated oven at 350° until brown.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: In large pot or Dutch oven, melt one stick of margarine and add rice.
Stir until rice is lightly browned.
Add cumin, chicken broth and water and bring to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Cover for ten minutes.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in frying pan and fry chicken until done.
Remove chicken and add to rice. Using same pan, fry onions, peppers and one tablespoon of cumin.
Add this to rice.
Season mixture and mix well.
Regular rice may be used but must be cooked for 20 minutes.

title: corn meal pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, meal and soda 3 times.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add salt to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Fold into cake mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Combine softened margarine and cheese.
Add cayenne pepper, salt and flour; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves, alternating with zucchini and raisins.
Chill 2 hours, then drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes (will freeze).

title: katie's favorite salsa(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on low or chop speed, stopping to stir 3 to 4 times.
Blend until thick consistency or chunky.
Total blending time is about 30 seconds.
Refrigerate; keeps 2 weeks.
Zero grams of fat! Serve with tortilla chips.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: juanita's fake steak
directions: Split roast in half lengthwise to resemble steak slice. Apply tenderizer	as directed.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Let	stand
at
room
temperature for 6 to 8 hours.	Turn every
few hours.
Preheat grill.
Grill meat at medium heat
for 20 minutes per side or until done to preference.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add boiling water.
Mix with peach jello.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Allow to cool.
Place sliced peaches in the filling mix and pour into pie shell that has been previously baked.
Top with whipped cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Instead of the usual steps of preparation, just dump all the ingredients in a bowl at one time.
Mix them well.
The result is delicious when mixed.
Turn into greased 9 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread loaf pan or into two 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch nut bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until bread tests done when skewer is inserted into the center.
Allow to cool 5 minutes in pan.
Turn out onto wire rack.
Banana Nut Bread freezes well and can be sliced while frozen if you do not plan to use the entire loaf at one time.

title: sponge shortcake - nummmmmm
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. In separate bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored (about 3 minutes) at high speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 minutes.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add other ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut in any desired shape.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: betty gardner's spice cookies(michael deceglie's grandmother's recipe)
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually to above.
Mix thoroughly. Roll in small, walnut size balls and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat in crock-pot on high for 2 hours. Reduce heat to low.
Stays warm all day.

title: quick stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds. Cook peppers in boiling, salted water for 5 to 8 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain.
Prepare rice mix as directed.
Chop corned beef and add to rice mix.
Stuff peppers with mix.
Bake in muffin pans, with 1/4-inch water, for 30 minutes.
Or a shallow pan in 1/4-inch water.

title: ham and cheese dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with parsley, dry mustard, hot sauce and mayonnaise.
Fold in ham and chill for about 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients 2 minutes.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and peanuts.
Just before serving, stir in apples.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until just blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped carrot casserole
directions: Chop and boil carrots until almost done, then drain. Melt butter, mustard and all dry ingredients in saucepan. Add milk. Then cook on medium-low, stirring until thick and bubbly. Stir in cheese. Melt. Combine mix with carrots. Put in casserole dish. Cover with French fried onions. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned pull taffy
directions: Combine sugar, Karo, water and cream of tartar.
Place over heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook, without stirring, to 265° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add coloring and flavoring, if desired.
Pour on greased platter or pie pan.
Cool until easily handled.
Pull into ropes until chalky and porous. Break or cut into bite-size pieces with scissors.

title: number puffs
directions: Take two heaping cups of patience

title: cooper's awesome potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
DO NOT ADD MILK OR SALT!
Cut cheese, ham, and salami into small pieces.
Mix with mashed potatoes.
Add eggs, 1/2 stick of butter, pepper, and Parmesan cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Cut up rest of butter and put on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: bubbi's morning cookies
directions: Boil for 3 minutes the following: sugar, butter, milk and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add cocoa, oats and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: christmas pear salad
directions: Divide pears into 2 glass bowls with juice.
In one bowl, sprinkle green food coloring and in the other use the red.
Stir gently to mix the coloring with the pears.
Set aside.

title: lemon pepper seafood kabobs
directions: Combine olive oil, lemon juice, parsley, thyme and pepper. Wrap each scallop with Prosciutto; secure with toothpick.
Place scallops and shrimp in dish.
Pour oil mixture over.
Cover and marinate 2 hours.
Alternate scallops, vegetables (cut in chunks) and shrimp on skewers.
Grill until seafood turns opaque; basting frequently, about 12 minutes, turning once.
Serve over long grain rice with pine nuts and lemon juice added.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add other ingredients and heat. Good served with chips.

title: grilled marinated turkey breast tenderloins(serves 4)
directions: Marinate turkey breasts (overnight or all day) in lime juice, mustard, garlic salt and butter.
Grill on low for approximately 20 minutes before turning for approximately 15 minutes.
Baste with marinade every 5 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook the beef in Crisco until brown in a 10-inch pan.
Drain the grease and return meat to the stove.
Add beef bouillon (can be made from 2 bouillon cubes and 2 cups of water), the catsup, garlic and salt to onion.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours on low heat until meat is tender.
Add the mushrooms. Mix 1/3 cup water and flour in a tightly covered container.
Stir mixture gradually into beef mixture.
Heat to boiling and stir constantly.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Prepare egg noodles according to package instructions.
Drain and toss with the butter.
Serve beef mixture over hot noodles.
Serve some hot biscuits or rolls on the side if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: grandmother smith's recipe for crab meat imperial
directions: Fold in crab meat to other ingredients.
Dab more mayonnaise on top, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 or 25 minutes.
Rich, lots of calories but delicious.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Line casserole dish with the mixture.
Precook frozen broccoli halfway and put on top of hamburger.
Mix cheese soup and milk together and put on top of broccoli.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, sugar and cocoa several times into mixing bowl.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Stir until smooth. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana-orange frost
directions: Peel and slice banana; place in bowl or blender and mash.
Add orange juice; beat until smooth.
Add milk and half the sherbet; beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 tall glasses; top each with scoop of sherbet.
Decorate each glass with orange slice and banana slice, if desired.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: all-bran bread
directions: Blend together and let rise.
Punch down and let rise.
Make into loaves and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 5 medium loaves.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken breasts in just enough water to cover them and cook until tender. Set aside to cool,

then pick off into pieces. Put carrots and potatoes in broth from cooked chicken and cook until tender. Add chicken pieces, drained peas and cream of chicken soup to carrots and potatoes in pot. Simmer for 15 minutes. Put mixture into one of the deep-dish pie shells and use other pie shell to cover. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: ultra creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Place broth and potatoes in saucepan, heat to a boil. Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain, reserving broth. Mash potatoes with 1/4 c. broth, cream, butter and pepper. Add additional broth, if needed, until desired consistency. Serves about 6.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except the chocolate chips and Crisco.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and Crisco together.
Dip the balls in the chocolate to coat.
Place on waxed paper to set.
Chill.

title: never fail devil's food cake
directions: Use as listed.
Do not stir until all ingredients are in pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cajun country red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in a very large, heavy kettle.
Add water; cover and soak overnight.

title: lazy cabbage roll casserole
directions: Place cabbage in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Brown together hamburg and onion; drain off fat.
Add rice, soup and water.
Mix and heat through, about 10 minutes, then pour over cabbage. Cover; bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Cook carrots for 8 to 10 minutes in a small amount of water. Drain; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes a big bowl full.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cover bottom of casserole with coarsely ground saltine crackers (about 30).
Place and spread out 1 quart oysters on saltines.
Salt and pepper oysters.
Cover oysters with layer of cracker crumbs.
Add half and half to just cover crumbs.
Dot top with butter.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Dip raw pieces of chicken
into
melted margarine, then roll in crumbs.
Place in well oiled, 9 x 13-inch baking dish, laying pieces side by side, not
crowding.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for an hour
or
until meat is brown and tender.

title: easy turkey casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
Combine soup, 1 cup cheese, pimento and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Add turkey and mix well.
Add noodles to turkey mixture and mix well.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: gene's delicious tea cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Shape dough into balls using a teaspoon of dough for each cookie.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and gently press down with hand.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
6-8 dozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Drain off oil.
In buttered casserole (2 to 3 quart), slice potatoes very thin on bottom.
Top with chops. Pour mushroom soup on next.
Mix Lipton soup in the water and pour over the rest.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour on top shelf.

title: hot buttered cranberry punch
directions: Mix sugar and spices with 1 cup of water and bring to boil. In large pan, crush cranberry sauce with fork and add remaining 3 cups of water.
Beat until smooth.
Add the pineapple juice and special syrup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot topped with dot of butter.
Add cinnamon sticks for stirrers if you wish.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts or 20 servings.
Great at winter holidays.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Add to margarine in mixing bowl.
Let stand overnight.
Add flour, then add pepper, Tabasco and Rice Krispies. Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten balls with fork.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: super zucchini bread
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour, wheat germ, nuts, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Gradually stir in flour mixture. Turn into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Remove to racks to cool.

title: curried four fruit bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter; add brown sugar and curry powder.
Drain and dry fruits; place in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add butter mixture.
Bake 1 hour uncovered.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Place 2 teaspoons margarine, brown sugar and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches.
Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup.
Heat in oven until melted.
Mix baking mix, applesauce and milk until dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes.
Spoon onto mixture in cups.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Invert on heatproof serving plate.
Yield:
12 biscuits.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Wesson oil and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, then fold in apples and nuts. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: five-layer dinner(diabetic recipe)
directions: In a casserole, layer potatoes, then beef, onions, corn and tomatoes.
Season layers with 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: joe's cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add flour and eggs alternately, mixing well.
Add water, if needed, to make dough soft.
Mix in vanilla. Knead on floured surface until stiff.
Roll out thin.
Cut with different shaped cookie cutters.
Decorate as desired.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Makes lots of cookies.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies; overlap cookies on cookie sheet to bake together.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine ground raisins and orange peel with sour milk. Alternate milk with combined dry ingredients.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Make well in center.
In small bowl, mix milk, pumpkin, butter and egg; add to well in flour mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon nuts over each.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pans.
Makes 12.

title: mexican shrimp
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large saucepan. Saute onions and pepper until soft.
Add garlic.
Add tomatoes and wine and season with cumin, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Add shrimp and simmer about 20 minutes, until shrimp are pink.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook, skin and debone chicken; cool.
In some of the chicken broth, cook onion and celery.
Cook spaghetti in water with a little oil to prevent sticking and boiling over.
Chop cooled chicken and add all ingredients in large bowl.
Put in large roaster, baking dish or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Spread pan then layer in bread. Top with meat, cheeses, dry mustard and salt. Veggies such as onion and red peppers, chopped, may be added.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put half of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of batter.
Pour remaining batter and spread to edges.
Cook until done at 350°, about 1 hour.

title: quick salsa dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Also makes a good baked potato topper.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Chop broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Snap green beans and slice zucchini into thin slices.
Chop onion.
Melt margarine in wok over low heat.
Add all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often, until vegetables are tender.
Enjoy served hot.

title: frozen strawberry punch
directions: Bring to a boil 9 cups of water; add 3 boxes of Jell-O and simmer until mixed well.
In another pan, bring to a boil 4 cups water and 4 cups sugar until it mixes well.
Mix the preceding ingredients together; add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix well; pour in 2 (1 gallon) plastic containers and freeze.
This can be frozen for weeks.
When ready to use, set out of freezer 2 to 3 hours before time to serve.
Add 1/2 ginger ale to each gallon of punch.
This recipe will serve approximately 40 guests.
Just repeat recipe for the number of guests that you are expecting.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler; add sweetened condensed milk.
When melted, add pecans and drop in small mounds on a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Melt Hershey's pieces and paraffin in double boiler.
Keep over low heat.
With a toothpick, dip mounds in chocolate and place on wax paper.
Store in tight container.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Mix green pepper, onion and celery.
Flake crabmeat, removing all shell.
Mix crabmeat, shrimp and vegetables.
Add mayonnaise and seasonings and place in greased casserole.
Cover with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Place cooked noodles in a 13 x 9 casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Beat egg and add milk and soup. Pour over noodles and bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Place chicken then broccoli in baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, soup and curry powder together and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and mixture bubbles.

title: molasses whoopie pies
directions: Beat molasses, eggs, sugar, shortening and vinegar.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in cup of hot coffee. Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with brown sugar and let cool.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour, baking powder, nuts and chocolate chips. Bake in an 8 x 10-inch cake pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Saute onion and green pepper approximately 2 minutes.
Return meat to skillet. Add tomatoes and bouillon cube(s).
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Simmer until tender (5 minutes), stirring occasionally.

title: cold blueberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip (1 cup).
Spread on bottom of crust.
Fill with 3 cups berries.
Combine 1 cup berries and water. Bring just to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Strain and reserve juice (1/2 cup).
Combine sugar and starch.
Gradually add juice and cool, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Cool slightly.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over berries and chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: punch-a-creme(alcoholic drink)
directions: Beat eggs with peel of lime in a large deep bowl until very light.
Remove lime peel.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add rum, then Angostura and stir briskly.
Place in clean bottles; cork well.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and melt margarine.
Mix crackers with margarine.
Cut cheese into bite size pieces.
In casserole alternate layers of broccoli, cheese and crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: good baked squash
directions: Boil squash in small amount of water until soft.
Drain and mash.
Saute bacon or ham with onion.
Add to squash along with eggs, milk and cracker crumbs.
Salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blackberry special pie
directions: Pour a quart of washed berries into pastry lined pie plate. Also pour brown sugar, flour, salt and a little nutmeg over berries.
Add top crust, slitting the center of top crust.
Press edges together.
Trim and rub cream over top crust.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until browned in 350° oven, about 30 to 35 minutes. You may use huckleberries, raspberries, blueberries, gooseberries, increasing sugar to desired sweetness.
(White sugar may be used instead a of brown.)
(Butter instead of cream may be rubbed over top crust.)
Yield:
8 - 10 servings.

title: christmas cut-outs
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in butter until mixture looks like cornmeal. Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Combine with flour and butter mixture.
Chill dough.
On lightly floured board, roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut and place on buttered sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: rice consomm
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add rice and stir until yellow. Add consomm and mushrooms.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325 degrees with lid on.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix boiling water and Jell-O. Set aside and cool. Mix the cake mix, oil and eggs. Then add the Jell-O mixture and mix well. Pour into greased pan. Cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Blanch squash whole until you can push a fork into it (do not cook too long).
Drain and cool squash.
Slice squash lengthwise; scrape out the meat with a spoon, leaving just a shell.
Mix together all ingredients.
Fill squash shells with mixture; heat for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese has melted.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda.
Cut shortening in flour mixture. Add yeast mixture, then buttermilk.
Pat into biscuits.
Cook at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pumpernickel beef dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Let set for 5 minutes, then put in center of round loaf of pumpernickel bread (which you have cut the center out of).
Serve.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
This is a special occasion dish and is enough stuffing for a large turkey.

title: dietetic grape jelly
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; add saccharine.
Bring 1 cup grape juice to a boil in saucepan; add to gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add the remaining grape juice, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Pour into jelly glasses; cool.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze in muffin tins or small molds.
Cover tins or molds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken on stove in water until tender; cube chicken. Cook noodles on the stove in boiling water until tender.
Saute onion and celery in 1 teaspoon margarine.
Combine chicken, noodles, onion, celery, soups and 1 cup milk in large baking dish. Add garlic salt and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of casserole.
Bake in moderate oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
A family favorite.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Blend butter, flour, salt, cream cheese and Blue cheese in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until smooth.
Cook broccoli; drain. Do not overcook.
Fold broccoli into cheese mixture.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Toss occasionally.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.
Good for large gatherings.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Note: Select eggplants that spring back after squeezing, are mostly free of blemishes, and have smooth skin.
They should feel heavy for their size; light plants will be mushy or full of seeds inside.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Grate cabbage, chop onion, salt and pepper to taste in large bowl.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients in oven safe pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 375°.
Sprinkle Tony Chachere's to taste.

title: brass rail salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, garlic powder, paprika, white pepper, dry mustard powder and salt.
Mix real good, then add vinegar, oil, tomato soup and onions.
Stir real good.
Put this in a large jar and shake well before using each time, as the oil comes to the top. Let set out for one day, then put in the refrigerator.
It will keep for a long time.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until creamy.
Add 1 egg; beat well. Add flour and another egg, and more flour until eggs and flour are used.
Beat mixture until creamy.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: francine's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, confectioners sugar and dates. Shape into balls and freeze.
In double boiler, melt wax and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and refreeze. Keeps frozen for months.

title: creole shrimp jambalaya
directions: Pour tomato sauce into the fried tomato paste.
Add fried onion and the next 9 ingredients; simmer a few minutes.
Add 1 cup water and bring to a hard boil.
Add rest of water, bring to hard boil, add shrimp and bring to boil again.
Add rice, bring to hard boil and stir.
Do not stir again.
cover, turn heat very low and let steam about 25 minutes, until rice is done, not gummy.
Keep covered.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onions and green peppers. Drain well.
Mix the jalapenos, tomato sauce and cheese in a saucepan and heat until the cheese is melted, stirring until mixed well.
Pour over beef and mix well.

title: rainbow ice creams
directions: In large bowl dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients until creamy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, starting and ending with flour.
Add 7-Up and lemon flavoring.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into oiled Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.
Do not open oven door.

title: pork vegetable bake
directions: Place potatoes and carrots in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Trim fat from steaks.
In large skillet, cook trimmings until about 2 tablespoons of oil accumulates.
Discard trimmings. In hot oil, brown steaks well on both sides.
In small saucepan, combine water, onion soup mix and soy sauce; bring to boil. Spoon half of soup mixture over the potatoes and carrots.
Top with steaks and spoon remaining soup mixture on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: date dainties
directions: Cook together dates, water, sugar and nuts until consistency of jam.
Set aside to cool.
Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients and oatmeal.
Mix until crumbly.
Firmly pat 1/2 of the mixture on a cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with date filling; add remaining crumbs and pat smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars or squares.

title: amazing beef
directions: Place roast (an inexpensive cut such as boneless chuck) and chopped garlic into slow cooker.
Dump entire jar of peppers (pepperoncini) and liquid over it.
Cook all day on low (10 to 12 hours).

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add a little water if needed.
Mix with chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one dish chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Veg-All, soups, 1 cup milk, the chicken and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, slice and cook until tender, then mash.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add tomatoes, pepper, onion, salt, brown sugar and bread crumbs.
Mix well and add mashed eggplant.
Place in a casserole and top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry wine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool and add cranberries, crushed pineapple, Port wine and nuts.
Cream the cream cheese with sour cream.
Add to jello; mix and chill.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix together sesame seeds and almonds on a cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven
to
minutes
until
browned. Crush noodles in bags (do not use seasoning packet).
Mix rest of ingredients with
cabbage
and onions.
Pour salad dressing over all and mix.
Let stand
at
least	one hour.
Best if it sets overnight in refrigerator.

title: lasagna pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add seasonings and tomato paste. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread rolls, top with 1/2 meat mixture and mix together cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Spread on top of meat mixture.
Top with remainder of meat mixture.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Blend together oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add cake mix, instant pudding and water.
Mix until all ingredients are combined.
Fold in poppy seed.
Turn into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: king crab quiche
directions: Line an unbaked pie shell with pastry.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside.
In a blender combine mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch.
Process until smooth.
Add cheese, onion and pepper, then blend at low speed for 2 to 3 seconds; just to combine.
Fold in crab meat.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top puffs up and is golden brown.
Remove from oven to rest 10 minutes before serving so custard can firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Pour all ingredients in crock pot and mix well.
Let cook on high for about 2 hours, and then on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add all remaining ingredients (except peas).
Cook and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add peas the last 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Peel as soon as possible; mash up.
Add sour cream and cheese; save a little cheese to put on top.
Add the Italian seasoning; mix well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top; bake until cheese is melted.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix dry ingredients with sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour cake batter into a tube pan suitable for microwave.
Microwave at High 14 to 15 minutes. Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 7 minutes cooking time.
Cool in pan. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix together and stir in all other ingredients.
Stir enough to dampen well. Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Slice potatoes; place in greased casserole dish.
Add salt and black pepper.
Crumble raw ground beef over potatoes.
Slice onion and green pepper; spread over ground beef.
Spread kidney beans over onion and green pepper.
Cover all with tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Top with cheese, if desired.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream margarine, egg, molasses and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful into sugar, coating all sides.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until crackled and golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: louisiana pinto beans
directions: Take pinto beans; soak in water overnight in a large sealed container.
Put in a larger boiler the next morning, adding onions, bell peppers, black pepper, salt and butter or margarine. Cook under a low fire with a top, adding your meats.
Use fat back with pieces of chopped ham.
Other choices of meat are ham hocks, salt meat or neck bones.
Let cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine 2 cups flour, the baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Toss berries with 1 tablespoon flour.
Beat 10 tablespoons of butter, the granulated sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla about 5 minutes.
Beat in flour in thirds, alternating with milk, using 1 cup.
Beat whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Fold in berries.
Pour into pan.
Bake until done, about 30 minutes.
Beat 4 tablespoons of butter, the cream cheese and a pinch of salt.
Beat in confectioners sugar, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons of milk.

title: waldorf salad with peanut butter dressing
directions: Combine apple, raisins and celery; set aside.
Make dressing in separate bowl.
Combine yogurt, peanut butter, vanilla and sweetener.
Whip dressing and pour over apple raisin mixture. Toss.
Makes 1 serving.
Counts as 1 fruit, 1 vegetable, 1 milk, 1 fat and 1 protein.

title: black jack venison jerky
directions: Venison and/or beef work very well for this recipe-cheaper cuts and scraps of lean venison are used.
Cutting of meat can best be accomplished with the meat partially frozen.
Cut meat into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Width and length is variable, depending on cut of meat.
Place meat in mixing bowl, mix in liberal amount of plain soy sauce, and mix in liberal amount of lemon pepper.
Allow to stand in refrigerator overnight (optional).
Using cookie racks in shallow baking pans; place meat strips on racks in pan covered with aluminum foil, making sure that adjacent pieces are not touching.
Place pans in oven for drying, usual time for drying is overnight for gas oven with modern burner controls on lowest setting or place in food dehydrator as per unit instructions.
Meat is done when dry throughout but not brittle.
Store in plastic bags in fridge.

title: thumb print cookie
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and egg yolk; add flour and salt.
Shape into 1 inch balls and dip in slightly beaten egg white, then roll in 1 cup finely chopped pecans.
With thumb press hole in each ball.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and put a teaspoon in the hole in center of cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Cut cheese and ham into blocks.
Place a slice of each inside roll.
Mix mustard, onion, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed and butter.
Heat and pour over rolls.	Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with a rolling pin between sheets of wax paper.
Prepare stuffing mix with orange juice (I make the orange juice, but the recipe calls for use of the concentrate) instead of water.

title: mac and tuna
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Let water come to a boil and add 1/4 teaspoon vegetable oil when macaroni is done.
Combine tuna, onions, eggs, mayo and salad cubes together in large bowl.
Serve chilled.

title: bread (rolls)
directions: In a large bowl sprinkle dry yeast.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir.
Then add water and egg.
Beat dough quick with spoon 25 strokes.
Cover bowl with towel and let rise for 2 to 4 hours.
Push down.
Add enough flour to handle.
Knead gently for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pinch off and make into rolls.
Place into baking pan and let rise 2 hours or more.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: caesar salad
directions: Make a paste of garlic, pepper, dry mustard and anchovies. Blend in egg (Egg Beaters may be used).
Stir in oil and lemon juice.
Toss romaine lettuce.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: skillet beef
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Slice small zucchini; lay over top of beef.
Smash tomatoes over top of zucchini; cover with cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted completely, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Heat chili and drain excess fat.
Melt cheese over double boiler and add tomatoes and chili in concentrated form.
Blend all ingredients.
When heated well, serve in chafing dish with chips.

title: old-fashioned hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix together sugar, corn syrup, cocoa, milk, margarine and salt.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Stirring occasionally, boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: no-bother buns
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in
lukewarm
water	plus 1 teaspoon sugar. Mix sugar, vegetable oil or shortening and salt with 2 cups water; heat to melt
sugar	and
salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Mix yeast with sugar and oil
mixture; stir into flour to make a soft dough.
Not much kneading is needed after flour absorbs liquids. Let rise for 1
hour
or
until
double.
Form
into even-size balls and let rise	until double on sheet pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each is added.
Add flour to baking powder and and add to butter mixture alternately with milk. Pour in 3 layer pans and bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until done.
Ice with Caramel Icing:

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Drain each when done.
Add Cheez Whiz and soups to this while still hot.
Combine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with shredded Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add all ingredients and stir.
Grease 3 (1-pound) foil pans. Divide into pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 43 minutes.

title: spinach spread
directions: Combine ingredients; chill overnight.
Serve on crackers of your choice.

title: low-fat oven-fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken, cutting breasts into halves crosswise and discarding skin and fat.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Brush chicken with yogurt, coating each piece with bread crumbs. Spray pan with Pam.
Put chicken in pan; try not to touch pieces together.
Bake at 450° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is brown and tests done.

title: country style steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces; roll in flour, salt, pepper and meat tenderizer.
Brown steak in skillet with oil.
Slice onion over steak.
Turn heat down; pour gravy over steak.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, or until steak is tender.
Onion may be omitted.

title: dump cake cobbler
directions: Put in layers in deep 13 x 9-inch pan, in this order: pineapple, pie filling, cake mix, pecans and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mama's plain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to butter.
Slowly add milk and water.
Beat until creamy.
Add flavoring.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with fresh fruit in season.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add other ingredients and cook 30 minutes until done, stirring often.

title: greek beans
directions: Fry hamburg, green pepper and onion until hamburg is done. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2-quart casserole in a 300° oven, uncovered.

title: grandma's angel biscuits
directions: Put all dry ingredients in bowl. Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in the warm water. Add extra flour if needed. Bake in greased pan at 450°. You don't have to let them rise before cooking, but they are better if you let them rise about 10 minutes. Store the rest of the dough in a tight container in refrigerator. Keeps up to 7 days.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container. Use 2 to 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through.

title: punch
directions: Prepare lemonade with directions on can.
Prepare jello with 4 times the amount of water.
Add pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pecan cookie balls
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter and powdered sugar. Add vanilla, flour, salt and pecans.
Blend well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes until slightly brown.
Remove from pan and roll hot cookies in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Butter a large flat pan or casserole dish.
Pat 1 1/3 cups stuffing mix on bottom of pan, then a layer of the cooked beans. Next, a layer of chicken, then pour over the canned milk and soup that have been blended together.
Brown 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add rest of the stuffing.
Top the casserole with this, then pour over the 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes more.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook until soft the zucchini with diced onion.
Beat eggs and add canned milk or half and half, melted butter, sugar and cracker crumbs. Add the egg mixture to the cooked zucchini along with grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix well and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple dream pie
directions: Combine coconut and butter.
Press on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes until coconut is golden.
Cool.

title: fake steak
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into large patties.
Wrap with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Brown on both sides.
Pour off drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup water in bowl, blending well.
Pour over meat.
Cook, covered, over low heat until done or bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: no fuss caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in a large (grocery) brown bag.
Combine sugar, syrup, salt and butter in a glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after every minute until mixture comes to a boil.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Shake bag.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake bag again.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Pour into large pan; stir to separate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion, pepper, pineapple and 1/2 of the walnuts.
Mix well and form into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in remaining walnuts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: tortilla beef roll-ups
directions: Spread one side of each tortilla with about 2 tablespoons of the horseradish dip, covering whole tortilla.
Top with 1 or 2 slices of beef.
Spread with another 2 tablespoons of dip.
Top with lettuce leaves.
Roll tortilla jelly roll style.
Place seam side down on platter.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Before serving, cut each roll-up crosswise into thirds.

title: inside-out chicken pot pie
directions: Brown and cut up chicken. Add frozen vegetables and soup. Cover and simmer until done.

title: glazed ham balls
directions: Have ham and pork ground fine. Add beaten egg, bread crumbs, milk and onion. Shape into balls. Place into shallow baking dish and baste with sauce. Bake at 375° for 50-60 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, until all added.
Mix well.
Add flour alternately with milk and flavoring.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Combine evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, flour and vanilla.
Cook until thick, stirring so mixture won't scorch.
Remove from heat; add coconut and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Frost cake when cool.

title: old fashioned apple fritters
directions: Pare, core and cut apples into eighths, then into thin slices. Mix flour, baking powder and salt and sift.
Add milk and egg gradually.
Stir apples into batter and drop by spoonfuls into hot vegetable oil.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef over medium-high heat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Continue to cook until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 2 hours or until the macaroni is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight.
Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients and cook 1-1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: aunt bill's apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, sour cream and flavorings. Sift together baking soda, salt and flour.
Carefully blend liquid and dry ingredients until blended.
Pour into tube pan and bake 80 to 90 minutes.
Carefully shake out of pan and cool on wire rack. This can be eaten immediately, but is best after one day when the brandy has mellowed.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together and pour over carrots. Refrigerate.

title: cavatina
directions: Brown chuck, sausage, green pepper and onion; drain.
Add soup, water, sauce and pepperoni.
Simmer. Mix with cooked noodles.
Divide in half and layer the Swiss and Cheddar cheeses, topping with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is lightly browned.

title: butterscotch peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In 8-inch square baking pan, place peaches and raisins; set aside.

title: peanut butter bites
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy in mixer.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to wet ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1/2 to 1 hour.
Make small balls; place on cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Put on racks to cool.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into meatballs.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix as you would a fruit cake.
Mix all dry ingredients, then add remaining fruits.
Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: southwestern crunch
directions: Place popped popcorn in a large bowl.
Melt butter in small pan. Add chili powder, oregano, cumin and cayenne pepper.
Drizzle over popcorn and toss lightly.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of a large or 2 small Pyrex dishes. Layer broccoli, carrots, water chestnuts, mushroom soup and chicken stock in dish.
In separate dish, mix flour, buttermilk and margarine until smooth.
Pour on top of chicken and vegetables. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: date nut squares
directions: Combine dates, water and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes or until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Add nuts.
Set aside.
Cream butter. Gradually add brown sugar and beat until blended.
Add flour, salt and oats.
Pack 2/3 of mixture evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread with date mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: cheese-stuffed sourdough bread
directions: Slice top from loaf and save.
Remove bread in pieces from inside loaf and wrap in foil.
Mix cheeses with remaining ingredients.
Fill cavity of loaf with cheese mixture.
Replace top of loaf and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. During final 30 minutes, place wrapped bread pieces in oven and bake with stuffed loaf.
Remove top, place loaf on serving tray, and surround with bread pieces.
Also good with Fritos Scoops.
If the sourdough loaf is small, use two.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, eggs, butter and milk.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and bread crumbs.
Pour into a greased baking dish; set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° until set, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni dinner
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in large cook and serve skillet, over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook ground chuck until browned.
Add onions, tomatoes, corn and macaroni and cook, covered 30 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chili powder, garlic salt and olives. Sprinkle with cheese and heat, covered for 5 minutes.
Serve in skillet. Serves 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the dry cake and nuts.
Sprinkle onto the apples.
Pour melted margarine over this.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: coffee cake bars
directions: Lay 1 package dinner rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then spread over the rolls. Cover the mixture with the other package rolls.
Pour 1/2 cup butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: big chunk bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients together with wooden spoon.
Add margarine, egg and vanilla to mixture and stir.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of flour onto the dates to keep them from sticking together and add dates, nuts and chocolate.
Stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and spread with fingers.
Mixture will be thick.
Cook at 325° for 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: miss daisy's beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Put beef in a large pot. Add all remaining ingredients, EXCEPT sharp cheese. Simmer 20 minutes. Pour into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Sprinkle sharp cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half.
Place on each cutlet. Starting with a short end, roll cutlet.
Tie if necessary. Combine flour and pepper.
Coat cutlets.
Melt butter over medium heat; add cutlets.
Cook until golden, about 3 minutes.
Add broth, wine and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer until chicken is cooked, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Place on dish and garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add water. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stirring as needed.
Brown tortillas on both sides.
Fill with filling.
Roll and lay in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cool and crumble.
Tear bread into pieces and spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Add sausage and cheese. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let set several minutes before cutting into squares. Serve with fresh fruit and muffins.
Ideal for weekend company.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Mix flour and margarine together along with pecans.
Make sure margarine is real soft.
Mash all 3 together with a fork in the baking pan.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Sit out to cool.
Make sure cream cheese is soft.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together with sugar, use mixer.
Spread this topping on top of the crust, then spread blueberries on top.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or more.

title: herbed vinegar
directions: *Some favorites are:
tarragon, basil, marjoram and dill.

title: trail mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, combine butter and both kinds of sugar.
With wooden spoon, beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir until blended.
Stir in oatmeal, raisins and sunflower kernels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart onto prepared pans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely on wire rack and store in airtight container.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: bonbons
directions: A day ahead, make
balls.
Stick
in toothpicks.
Place on waxed paper and freeze.
Next
day, dip in melted chocolate and paraffin, using while hot.
Place on waxed paper.

title: dill dip for vegies
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix sour cream and mayo.
Grate onion.
Add onion and juice to bowl; add seasoned salt and dill weed.
Mix well and rechill about 1 hour.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Cut up onion and green pepper. Fry with hamburger. Drain fat. Add tomatoes, spaghetti seasoning and mushrooms.
Cook until done. Cook noodles.

title: lena's miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender. Blend well. Pour into a 10-inch buttered pie plate. Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes. A crust will form on the bottom, a filling in the middle and the coconut will rise to the top.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Use 2 tablespoons bacon drippings; when hot, add water and vinegar.
When it comes to a boil, pour little of the mixture into the dry ingredients; stir well to avoid lumps.
Put all back into skillet and let come to a boil to thicken.
Pour over the cooked potatoes, hard-boiled eggs and crumbled bacon.
Place into greased dish and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made the day before and heated before serving.

title: crunch pieces
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put layers of crackers on foil-lined 15 x 10-inch pan.
Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake for 7 minutes (watch carefully).
Remove from oven and spread morsels on top of hot crackers with back of spoon. Let come to room temperature and then cool in refrigerator. Break into small pieces.
Can put wax paper between the broken pieces when storing them in a closed container or plastic bag in the refrigerator.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Press with a fork and bake only until brown.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and water for a few minutes.
Pour hot mixture over 1 package of lemon Jell-O.
Let partly congeal.
Add the whipped cream.
Add pecans and grated cheese according to taste.
Chill until set.

title: red beans & rice
directions: Mix first 14 ingredients in a large pot.
Cook over low heat for one hour and serve over hot cooked rice.

title: old virginia fresh peach ice cream
directions: Pare and stone 1 quart of very soft peaches. Add to them 2 cups of sugar and mash them thoroughly. When ready to freeze, add 2 quarts of rich cream. (Freeze in a hand-turned freezer.) When frozen, this will fill a dish holding 4 quarts.

title: classic fruit salad
directions: Wash and cut all fruit.
Combine in large bowl with raisins and walnuts.
Sprinkle with lemon juice to avoid discoloration. Combine yogurt and honey and serve as a side dressing or toss with salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: On wax paper, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Core pears but do not peel; chop fairly fine (there should be approximately 3 cups).
In a medium mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; beat in the eggs until blended.
Stir in flour mixture, in several additions, alternately with the coffee just until smooth; fold in the pears.

Turn into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; sprinkle batter with Streusel Topping (recipe to follow). Bake in preheated 350° oven until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean; 45 to 50 minutes.
Place on wire rack to cool.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and core peppers; set aside.
Fry hamburger (break up while cooking) with onion, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper. Drain.
Mix well with cooked rice.
Adjust salt and pepper to taste.
Combine with 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Fill peppers to mound on top.
By tablespoon add remaining tomato sauce to cover top of mixture.
Place peppers close together in a baking dish with water just to cover bottom of dish.
Bake, covered, 1 hour in a 350° oven until peppers are done.

title: grandma's soup
directions: Boil the shanks in water with spices until meat is cooked (about 1 1/2 hours).
Pour in equal amounts of tomato juice (1/2 can) and water (1/2 qt.).
Cook mixture down until it is reduced by half.
Add cooked elbow macaroni, and the left over water (1/2 qt.) and mix well.
Add 1 pint sour cream that is mixed with left over tomato juice.
Ready to serve,
Yum! Yum!

title: corn casserole(serves 10)
directions: Mix all together and place in baking dish.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lamb and white bean soup
directions: Put beans in a large heavy pot and cover with about 2-inches of cold water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove pot from heat and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain beans in a colander and discard the soaking water.
Return beans to pot in which they were cooked.
Add all remaining ingredients except cabbage and salt. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer an additional 30 to 40 minutes until beans are very tender.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Bake custard.
Use 4 egg yolks, stir and put in nonstick pan, half and half and juice of 1 lemon or 1/3 cup lemon juice.
Add slowly to milk/egg mixture. Cook over medium heat to a slight boil, not real thick.
Cool and add to fruit and stir.
Whip whipping cream.
Add sugar and whip, then add to mixture.
Chill overnight.
Excellent!

title: alaska tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook onions and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add salt, pepper, pimento, flour and milk.
Stir and cook until slightly thick.
Add chicken and soup.
Pour over cooked spaghetti, drained well.
Stir and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In lightly greased casserole (1 1/2-quart), combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, stirring frequently for 1 hour.
Complete cooking time is 2 1/2 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In large bowl, layer in order of ingredients, noting to spread mayonnaise as frosting a cake.
This seals the salad.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix well 10 minutes before serving.

title: italian creme layer cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour, buttermilk, oil, baking soda and vanilla.
Fold in coconut, nuts and beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add sour cream and mix until smooth.
Add apples and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into pie crust.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil until skins pop and sauce is desired thickness.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of 8-inch Teflon coated pan with uncooked oatmeal.
Cover oatmeal with mixture as directed.
Save Grape-Nuts cereal for later.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle cobbler with Grape-Nuts.
Bake for additional 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: seven layer jello
directions: Odd Layer:
1 1/2 cups boiling water and Jell-O.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix together flour and melted butter. Mix together eggs and sugar.
Mix eggs and sugar separately, then add to butter/flour mixture.
Mix together well. Add cranberries and nuts. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool well before cutting.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Then drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until light brown.
Mix in separate bowl the butter and garlic.
Remove from cookie sheet. Take butter-garlic mixture and paste over each biscuit.
Then enjoy!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and peel.
Mash potatoes and add butter, sugar, salt, cinnamon, egg yolks, milk, juice and lemon flavoring.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold gently but thoroughly into potato mixture.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake 15 minutes at 400° and then reduce heat to 375° for 30 minutes.
When a knife inserted just off center comes out clean, the pie is done.

title: sour cream tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs and blend eggs and vanilla with butter mixture.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with sour cream to the butter and egg mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Roll out on lightly floured surface 1/4 inch thick. Cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except crackers. Spread in a long casserole dish.
Crush cheese crackers and mix with melted margarine, if desired.
Spread crackers over vegetables.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: creamy ham casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into buds (about 4 cups).
Cook covered in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and combine ham and mushrooms in medium saucepan.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter, stir in flour, add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese and sour cream to sauce.
Stir well until cheese melts.
Combine with cauliflower and ham mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and remaining oleo. Sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes or until hot.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, vinegar and salt until boiling, stirring constantly.
Add butter, then slowly add cheese.
Cut in small pieces, stirring until melted.
Add chopped pimentos; let cool until warm.
Pour into containers and store in refrigerator.
Makes 5 butter containers full.

title: candied yams with cider
directions: Cook yams in boiling water about 20 minutes, until barely tender. Peel and cut in half lengthwise. Arrange in a buttered baking dish. In a saucepan combine cider, brown sugar and butter, bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Pour over yams in baking dish and bake at 375 for 45 minutes. Baste yams several times during baking with syrup.

title: fluffy sour cream pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Stir in sour cream and soda; combine other dry ingredients and stir into sour cream mixture.
Add butter and beat 30 seconds with electric mixer.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto a hot, lightly buttered griddle.
Turn when tops are bubbly and edges look cooked.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and process until mixture is smooth.
Makes 14 ounces.
Use in any recipe calling for sweetened condensed milk.
Keeps in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a heated greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake topped brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Spread into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In small bowl, beat cheese, butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over brownie batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
Cool and top with Chocolate Glaze.

title: baked scalloped oysters(mrs. orna d. banks)
directions: Combine oyster liquid and enough milk or cream to make 1 cup.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix Hidden Valley Ranch lo-cal, oil, lemon pepper, dill weed and garlic salt.
Break pretzels, add to mixture.
Make sure all pretzels are coated.
Spread on a tray.
Bake about 30 minutes to 1 hour, until toasted.
Cool and serve.
Bake at 350°.

title: frozen lemon delight
directions: Butter a pie pan well and sprinkle fine graham cracker crumbs into pan.
Shake to cover buttered surface well.

title: green beans (middle eastern)
directions: Saute onions in a little oil.
Put tomatoes in after sauteed onions; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add green beans after sauteing; add salt and pepper.
Simmer a couple of hours.
Keep adding water so mixture does not dry and burn.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In a large baking pan, shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Makes about 8 servings.
(Also terrific with Lipton Recipe Secrets onion soup mix.)

title: charleston cheese
directions: In a bowl, mix mayonnaise, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and onions. Put mixture into a greased quiche dish. Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and top with crumbled bacon. Serve with crackers.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and place in bottom of baking pan. Mix the remaining ingredients and place over the first layer of ingredients in the baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: adkin's tartar sauce
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: shell macaroni salad
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Combine with cooked macaroni, both jars Cheez Whiz and tomatoes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: beets with orange sauce
directions: Cook juice of beets, sugar and cornstarch; stir until thickened.
Add orange juice and beets; cook until thickened.
Add butter.
Add salt.
Serve hot.
Always a favorite at our house!

title: self crust pumpkin
directions: Beat with mixer 2 minutes until smooth.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Add rinsed anchovies and stir.
Anchovies will become pasty.
Add tomato paste, 2 cans (paste) of water, tomato sauce and crushed tomatoes; also parsley and pepper.
Slow simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Then add tuna; mix well and simmer another 30 to 45 minutes. Serve over spaghetti or fettucini.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce at least 30 minutes or overnight.
Drain well.
Roll in 1/4 cup of sugar and wrap bacon strips around and secure with toothpick.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Can be baked ahead and reheated at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: crunchy crisps cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add vanilla and egg; beat until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and baking powder to creamed mixture.
Add rolled oats and mix thoroughly.
Add grated coconut and blend well into dough.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: candy chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart bowl on High 2 minutes; stir.
Continue 1 or 2 minutes until smooth, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.
Microwave remaining 2 ounces bark with oil.
Drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Store at room temperature.

title: seafood creole
directions: Make roux by stirring flour and shortening over medium heat until well browned.
In a large pan, mix roux, water, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add celery, bell pepper, okra, onions and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley, green onion, seafood, salt, red and black pepper and Tabasco.
Cook 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: ann's chicken breasts supreme
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup. Pour this over chicken.
Place bacon and beef over entire mixture.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan; drain. Stir in water, tomatoes, carrots, mushrooms, barley, garlic and oregano. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until barley is tender. Season to taste. Stir in cubed cheese spread until melted. Garnish as desired. Serve with sliced Italian or French bread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain.
Add both cans of soup and stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Slice enough Velveeta cheese to cover the top of the pan and place on top of the hamburger mixture.
Cover the top with Tater Tots.
Bake in the oven for 15 minutes or until the Tater Tots are brown.
The oven temperature should be 425°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix together in saucepan and heat thoroughly.

title: "sliders"
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add soup mix and cheese.
Slice buns in half; fill with meat mixture.
Replace tops.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add pickle slices.

title: hobo bread
directions: Pour boiling
water
over
raisins
and soda; let stand overnight (use a large container).	In the morning, add sugar, salt, oil
and
flour; mix.
Grease and flour 6 (1-pound) cans (tall coffee cans);
fill 1/2 full.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cut	wax
paper
for
bottoms
of can.
Let stand 15 minutes after
removing
from oven.
After cold, wrap in Saran Wrap and put back in cans to store or freeze.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and onions together in enough water to cover until tender.
Chop meat.
Return to broth and add all ingredients, except corn.
Cook approximately 1 hour.
Add corn 15 minutes before serving time.
Freezes well.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients about 2 minutes on medium speed until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mincemeat crescents
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese until well blended. Mix in flour.
Shape dough into smooth ball.
Wrap in aluminum foil and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter.
Place about 1 teaspoon of mincemeat in center of each round.
Fold over and press edges together.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll cookies in mixture.
Cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: stuffed grilled hamburgers
directions: Mix together hamburger, egg, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and bread crumbs.
Shape into 10 thin hamburgers.
Dice onion, sausage, cheese and mushrooms; then mix and sprinkle on half the burgers.
Top with second burger and seal the edges. Cook on a grill until well done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine all ingredients except rum and boiling water.
Freeze at this point, if desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: You may use more butter and mayonnaise if you need too.

title: impossible brunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9-inch).
Spread spinach or broccoli in plate.
Beat yogurt, cottage cheese, baking mix, margarine and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Before baking, top with tomato; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Then, bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot dog and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, celery, onion and hot dogs.
Stir in mayonnaise and mustard.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chicken should be cooked, boned and chopped, then marinated in French dressing for 2 hours before putting salad together.
Cook rice in chicken broth until tender.
Put all ingredients together and chill well before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 50.

title: hot mustard
directions: Beat egg in small saucepan.
Add salt and mustard slowly under low heat.
Stir in vinegar.
(If too hot, it will curdle.)
Take off fire as it thickens to a nice mustard consistency.
(Note:
It will thicken a little more as it cools.)
Pour all at once into a jar with a laminated top (not tin).
Jelly jars are good. Refrigerate.
Will last 2 to 3 months in refrigerator.
Before using, let stand at room temperature.
Enjoy.

title: 5 layer dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix cans of beans and spread in pan for bottom layer.
Next, mix avocados with lemon juice, Tabasco, salt and pepper; spread this mixture on top of bean layer.
Next, mix salad dressing with sour cream; spread on top of avocado mixture, then top with tomatoes, olives and onions, then spread both cheeses on top to finish layers.

title: nell's gumbo
directions: Make roux using hot oil; add flour.
Stir until color of copper penny.
Add vegetables, except tomatoes and okra.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add the water; let simmer at least 1 hour.
Add shrimp.
After 10 minutes, add crabmeat.
Salt to taste; add pepper.
Add chopped okra and tomatoes.
Cook for at least 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, add gumbo file to individual bowls (about 1/2 teaspoon).
Pour gumbo in bowl and serve with rice.

title: pork adobo
directions: Rinse pork and set aside.
In large pot brown fat from parts of pork chunks.
When oil is hot (released from pork chunks), remove fat and saute garlic and onion.
Add pork chunks and brown, stirring periodically.
When pork has browned, drain oil and add vinegar, soy sauce and pickling spice.
Cover and set heat at medium and let pork steam.
When steaming, the meat will release its own juice.
Check periodically and stir.
When juice has turned to basically oil, adobois ready (about 20 minutes).
Drain oil and serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, eggs, bacon and sprouts in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix oil, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, onion and ketchup and chill. Pour dressing over salad when serving.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in water.
Add biscuit mix and beat.
Add mustard and 1 cup cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack before slicing.

title: easy dessert
directions: Melt margarine in long pan.
Break graham crackers in melted margarine.
Pour butterscotch morsels over crackers.
Next sprinkle coconut over and pecans.
Pour over all condensed milk. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and slightly brown.
Chill before cutting in squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and squash together.
Cook squash until done. Drain water off.
Cook and drain sausage.
Mix squash and sausage together, then mix mushroom soup until it is not dry.
Put all these together, then sprinkle either crushed potato chips or crackers over the top.
Then put cheese on top of that.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: low-fat salsa
directions: Puree crushed tomatoes; add remaining ingredients and then refrigerate at least 1 hour to properly blend all flavors.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Mix and pat first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
