Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Add rice and continue to mix.
Layer chicken on rice/soup mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for 1 more hour.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Beat batter for 4 minutes. Pour into buttered, lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 340°.
Cool 30 minutes in pan.
While cake is still in pan, pour boiled mixture of last 4 ingredients on top of cake. Cool 30 minutes.
Loosen cake.
Turn out onto plate.
This cake is pure ambrosia!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift salt and flour together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Blend in vinegar and baking soda.
Bake in a greased and floured layer pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: company pork chops
directions: Heat oil in skillet; brown chops on both sides.
Add onion, garlic, orange juice, vinegar, paprika, honey, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup broth; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove chops to platter; keep warm.
Gradually stir remaining 1/2 cup broth into flour.
Stir mixture into drippings in skillet; cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over chops.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender except for coconut.
Cover and blend on low speed for 4 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into ungreased jelly roll pan (15 x 11-inch). Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients in a 14 x 10 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Mix together all liquid ingredients (except water).
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients.
Pour 2 cups cold water over all of it.
At this point the cake looks like a terrible mistake, but it is all right.
Mix everything through with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Beat egg until thick.
Add drained fruit cocktail and 1/2 cup reserved liquid.
Stir in flour mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square cake pan. Combine pecans and brown sugar, mix well and sprinkle over top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp log
directions: Lay cream cheese out to soften.
Cut shrimp into small pieces. Chop olives and green onion into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and shape into log.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken wings marinated
directions: Marinate overnight in refrigerator. Barbecue on low heat.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, green pepper, onion and celery.
Add tomatoes, chili beans and seasoning.	Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, shredded cheddar cheese, diced olives and hot sauce.

title: cauliflower in hot cheese sauce
directions: Lightly steam cauliflower until tender, but still crisp.
In saucepan, mix together skim milk and flour.
Cook on low to medium heat until sauce thickens.
Add paprika, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper to saucepan with milk mixture; stir thoroughly.
Add cheese and stir to blend.
Place cauliflower on a serving platter and top with the sauce.
Sprinkle paprika over top for garnish effect.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: chili
directions: Put all ingredients together and simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo well in one bowl. In another bowl mix pudding, Cool Whip and milk, then combine both bowls.
Crush Oreos.
Layer cookies and add filling between layers (3 layers of cookies and 2 layers of filling), beginning and ending with cookie crumbs.
Can put in flowerpot and put in artificial flowers.
Chill.

title: casserole bread
directions: Scald milk and stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm.
Put water into a bowl; sprinkle in yeast; stir.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture.
Add flour; stir until well blended (about 2 minutes).
Cover; let rise 40 minutes in a warm place. Stir batter down.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix altogether and chill before serving.
Can add chopped maraschino cherries for a Christmas looking salad.

title: orange julius
directions: Add all ingredients in a blender.
Mix until the ice is all crushed.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings and mix.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Stays moist for days.

title: mom's quick chocolate cake
directions: Put in saucepan the chocolate, water and butter and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Place in bowl to cool slightly, then add rest of ingredients all at once.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overcook or cake will be dry!

title: elaine's chocolate delight with oreos
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and spread in pan for crust.
Combine cream cheese and whipped topping.
Spread half over cookies.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over 1st layer.
Combine remaining cream cheese and whipped topping with nuts, if desired.
Spread over pudding.
Decorate top with Oreo cookies, crushed or whole.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook over moderately hot heat, stirring constantly, until meat is brown.
Add bouillon and green peppers.
Cover closely and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 3 minutes longer.
Blend together cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Add to skillet and cook 3 or 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly, until mixture is hot and sauce is thickened.
Serve at once with hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: granny's homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt and shortening until smooth.
Add yeast, water, the other cup of water and enough flour (plain flour) to make a good elasticized consistency.
Put on floured board and work out real good, using hands to really work it down good.
Work until the consistency is good, but not dry.
Place in bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Then, put on floured board again and work it down real good, but not too dry.
Make into biscuits and turn in oil in baking pan.
Let biscuits rise until double in bulk.
Bake in oven at about 300° or 350°.
Not too fast, but not too slow.
You may need to adjust your oven as you know best.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking dish or pan.
Skin side up. In a separate bowl; mix other ingredients and spread over chicken. Baste often.
Bake covered 1 hour, then uncovered 1 hour in a 300° oven.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Mix egg whites and cream of tartar until foaming.
Add sugar. Mix until stiff.
Add crumbled soda crackers, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Pour in a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix the pineapple preserves and Cool Whip.
Spread over top.
Sprinkle with coconut. A cherry here and there looks pretty.

title: mediterranean marinated vegetables
directions: In a deep, straight-sided salad bowl, layer vegetables.
Pour on salad dressing.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Toss before serving; garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all together except 7-Up. Beat with a big spoon (not a mixer), then fold in the 7-Up and stir until real thick. Pour in greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook whole zucchini in boiling water for almost 10 minutes, or until tender; drain.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop center portion; set aside.
Saute mushrooms and reserve zucchini.
Preheat broiler.
Fill shells, using approximately 1/4 cup filling; sprinkle with cheese.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: lima bean bake
directions: Wash beans.
Add 1 1/2 quarts of water and cook until tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add salt after first hour of cooking.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add rest of ingredients to beans. Pour into casserole; season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg yolks and oil.
Add flour, water, cinnamon, nutmeg and pineapple.
Beat well by hand (not mixer).
Add nuts and fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add sugar, a small amount at a time.
Add vanilla, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Turn oven to 350° before starting.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in iron skillet at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: stoby's gumbo(conway, arkansas)
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
After it is cooked, add:

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce in large dish (casserole type).
Layer with water chestnuts and bell pepper.
You may want to sprinkle a little cheese here (I do).
Continue with green onions.
Top with mayonnaise, mixed with Parmesan cheese (to taste).
Sprinkle bacon bits and shredded cheese over top.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1/4-inch slivers.
Brown in skillet with small amount oil, salt and pepper.
Add bouillon cubes, water and onion. Cover and let simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
(If it cooks dry, add more water.)
Add celery and bell pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend and add cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Cook until it thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add slightly beaten eggs.
Add bananas, then flour.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: three day cake
directions: Bake in round layer pans.
Split layers; you must have 4 layers.

title: german bean and sausage soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Add carrots, potatoes, parsley, pepper and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add sausage, beans and reserved bacon; heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 (1 1/4-cup) servings.

title: venison with eggs(a man's breakfast)
directions: Slice venison 1/2 inch thick.
Salt, pepper and sprinkle with flour.
Pound in seasoning.
Place meat in oiled heavy skillet over medium heat.
Cover with an inverted pie plate and leave to brown 5 minutes.
Remove pie plate; turn and cook 5 minutes.
Remove meat and drop the eggs into the skillet; add 2 or 3 drops of water. Cover with pie pan again.
Steam the eggs 3 minutes without turning.
Can use same skillet after removing eggs to make a pan of gravy.
This is good.

title: angel food cake
directions: Set out tube pan; don't grease.
Measure and sift 3 times flour and confectioners sugar.
Measure into large bowl egg white, cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until foamy.
Gradually add 2 teaspoons at a time, sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in vanilla and almond extracts.
After flour and confectioners sugar is sifted 3 times, sift over meringue mixture.
Fold in gently just until flour and sugar mixture disappears.
Rush batter into pan and cut through with a knife.
Bake until top springs back when touched.
Invert on funnel and let cool completely.

title: peanut butter blooms
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar together. Mix all ingredients, except candy and sugars. Shape dough into balls and roll in sugars. Bake on Pam sprayed cookie sheet in 375° oven for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and put 1 Hershey's Kiss on top. Return to oven for about 2 to 5 minutes.

title: the greatest waffles
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add the beaten eggs.
Melt the butter and add it, then the milk.
Cook in a well-greased waffle iron.
Have the iron very hot before filling with the mixture.
Serve with maple syrup.
Makes 6 waffles.

title: granola #1
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread soft cream cheese in the bottom of a shallow 1-quart casserole dish, then add the following ingredients in layers: refried beans, salsa and then Cheddar cheese.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate peanut delight
directions: In bowl, mix cake mix, melted butter, milk and egg. Add 3/4 cup peanuts. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool. In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, condensed milk and vanilla until smooth. Fold in 3 cups Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Top with remaining Cool Whip and peanuts. In a microwave-safe bowl, melt the chocolate chips and butter on high for 1 minute or until melted. Stir in vanilla until smooth. Drizzle over cake. Refrigerate.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix the first
ingredients and beat to dissolve. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix
well.	May
be put in mold or shallow pan and
cut
in
squares.	This will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: civet de poulet
directions: Trim chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Marinate 8 hours in a mixture of the garlic, oregano, salt, pepper, vinegar, oil, prunes, olives, capers and bay leaves.
Pour into roasting pan in a single layer.
Combine sugar with wine.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook. Add parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yum yum salad(holiday salad)
directions: Evaporated milk must be refrigerated overnight.
Whip until thick.
Beat the milk; add cream cheese; beat.
Set aside.
Cook pineapple, sugar and jello.
Let cool for 10 minutes or so.
Mix two together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Skins may be removed if preferred. Melt margarine or butter or put oil in shallow baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture and arrange in a single layer in same pan.
Bake at 375°, basting occasionally, for 40 minutes (30 minutes if using boneless chicken breasts).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add
broccoli
to butter and onion; cook a few minutes. Add rice and mushroom soup.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Mix and pour into 2-quart casserole dish and top with bread filling.	Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large slow cooker. Stir to combine. Cover. Cook on high 2 hours and then on low 6 to 8 hours. Serve with rye bread.

title: easy brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Set oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in a mixing bowl and stir together.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until barely done.
Cool in pan.
Makes 16 (2-inch) brownies.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars, honey, egg, milk and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; mix together. Stir in oats, coconut, dates, wheat germ and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes for soft cookies.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: danish dessert
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water.
Bring to boil, then add fruit.

title: chocolate spectacular
directions: Mix together flour, nuts and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool and set aside.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries, apple juice, sugar and allspice in medium size nonreactive saucepan.
Bring to boiling. Lower heat. Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Add chopped apple. Cook 5 minutes more. Serve warm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 1/2 an hour.
Makes 1/2 gallon of sauce.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck with peppers and onions; drain. Add mixed vegetables, corn,
soup and cheese. Heat until cheese is melted. Cook noodles until tender, mix with other ingredients. Bake until hot.

title: barbecued deer chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Remove and replace in baking dish. Brown onions and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until flavors are well blended, about 15 minutes. Pour sauce over chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Put eggs in top of double boiler; add vinegar and sugar.
Beat constantly until mixture is thick and smooth.
Remove.
Add butter and cool. When
mixture is cold, fold in whipped cream, fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into dish.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: eggplant and feta salad
directions: Put the oil, cumin and coriander into a bowl.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste.
Brush both sides of the eggplant slices with the special oil and cook on a hot preheated grill for 3 - 4 minutes on each side until soft and lightly charred.

title: spinach in shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove insides and fill with souffle.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in buttered casserole for 30 minutes.

title: blender lemon pie
directions: Blend until smooth in blender.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: kiesh
directions: Place cubed bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add meat and any of the extras.
Beat eggs with milk and salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and meat and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
If making in 2 smaller pans, shorten the baking time.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and soak pears in water with salt for 1 hour.
Remove pears from salt water; let drain.
Place sugar and vinegar in a large pot; stir.
Add all other ingredients to the sugar-vinegar mixture.
Pour pears on top.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour, stirring constantly.
Wash, then boil, at least 4 to 5 pint jars and lids (use rims and caps with rubber seals).
Place pear relish into hot jars and seal tight.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix in large bowl with chopped onion, pimento and green pepper.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar.
Add to beans with thawed peas and pepper.
Marinate at least 8 hours.
Great to double for picnic or dinner.

title: pepper casserole
directions: In frypan, place sausage links in 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Pour off water and fat.
Brown sausage.
Cut up in chunk size.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven in large pot for 1 1/2 hours, adding water as needed so it won't stick, stirring occasionally.
Serve with noodles or rice.
A crock-pot may be used also for all day cooking.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs (room temperature) until very fluffy.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat in soda, extracts and sour cream.
Flour and grease an angel food cake pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Leave in pan to cool before removing.
Do not turn pan upside down!

title: bunny's elephant stew(serves 3,800)
directions: From an old Swedish cookbook.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix cool whip with instant pudding.
Stir in bananas last. Then add
condensed milk.
Layer your large casserole dish with vanilla wafers.
Then a layer of the mixture. Then a layer of vanilla wafers.
Then another layer of mixture, until it is used up.
Line the edged of the bowl with vanilla wafers as you do the layers.
Then top off with cool whip if you have extra cool whip or vanilla wafers.

title: cream cheese tortillas
directions: Spread cream cheese on tortillas.
Spoon picante sauce on top of cheese.
Smear around.
Roll up tortillas.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Spear with a toothpick.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla in large bowl; blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set, covering outer edges with foil to prevent overbrowning, if necessary.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together thoroughly and put in bottom of pie shell.
Save a little of the mixture to sprinkle on top.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Heat milk until it coats spoon.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture and add beaten egg yolks.
Cook mixture until it thickens.
Add vanilla and butter.
Mix together and pour into pie shell.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and the milk; set aside. Process the onions and bell peppers, then the shrimp. Combine everything together and taste for seasoning.

title: lasagna baked by mom
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients (following down from ground meat).
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread with half the cottage cheese filling; add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat the layers. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes. Serves 12.

title: yam balls
directions: Mix yams, sugar and pineapple together.
Take marshmallows and cover with potatoes.
Roll in coconut.
Take margarine and grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine in a large bowl Crisco, brown sugar, vanilla, milk and 1 egg.
Beat at medium speed until creamy. Add flour, salt and baking soda until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together the poppy seed, soup and sour cream.
Pour over the chicken in the pan. Mix together the crackers and margarine. Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: santa's slush
directions: Blend at high speed in electric blender half each of first four ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch square dish.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Break into chunks.
Add club soda; stir.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.

title: mark's favorite chicken
directions: Put bouillon cubes in hot water.
While waiting for that to dissolve, mix together all dry ingredients, except for gravy mix. Coat chicken in seasonings.
Cook chicken after spraying pan with nonstick spray.
Cook at least 6 minutes on high for each side, turning every 3 minutes until chicken is done.
Add lemon juice to chicken bouillon.
Pour over chicken on medium heat.
Cook both sides while juice is boiling, 4 minutes each.
Sprinkle gravy mix over chicken and juices.
Boil for 1 minute.
Turn off heat and cover, stirring occasionally during the 1 minute.
Sauce will thicken to form a gravy.
Serve over noodles or rice or eat it alone with side dish.

title: creamed tuna
directions: Thoroughly drain tuna, break up into large chunks.
Mix soup with milk and stir until completely smooth.
Fold in tuna. Arrange broccoli in an ovenproof serving dish.
Top with soup, milk and tuna mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and bread crumbs are nicely browned.

title: tuna roni
directions: Prepare Golden Wheat according to package directions; add tuna, peas and lemon juice.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Make sure you use English peas.

title: pistachio salad(nice for st. patrick)
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator overnight.
Quick and easy.
Serves 8 to 10.
Delicious.

title: broken glass jello
directions: To each box of Jell-O, add 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 cup boiling water.
Prepare each box separately and refrigerate in separate bowls.
Heat milk, sugar and gelatine almost to a boil.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut the flavored Jell-O into pieces and place in pan (9 x 13-inch pan).
Pour the milk mixture over the Jell-O. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: microwave brownie pie
directions: Cook
chocolate
and
butter
in a 4-cup dish on Medium 1 1/2 to	2
minutes.
Stir in sugar.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs;	return to hot mixture.	Stir in flour, baking powder,
salt,
vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a 2-quart round dish,
lightly
greased.
Cook on Medium or Slow Cook 7 minutes. Turn
dish	2
times.
Then
cook on High 3 minutes. Cool and cut into wedges.

title: hobo hamburgers
directions: Wrap in foil and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or bake until patties are done and vegetables are tender.

title: quick cinnamon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl and add other ingredients. Pour batter into 8 X 8 inch square pan.
Sprinkle with topping and bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift first five ingredients together.
Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Add the buttermilk and yeast which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix with spoon until flour is moistened. Do not overmix.

title: swiss alpine quiche
directions: Combine cheese and flour.
Layer half of broccoli, ham and cheese in the pie shell.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle onion on top. Combine milk, eggs and seasoning ingredients; pour over mixture. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cake
directions: Blend cake
mix, water, oil and eggs in a large bowel on low speed 30 seconds.
Pour into pans. Bake on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cake cool, then put the frost on it.

title: flour tortillas(tortillas de harina)
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and salt in a medium bowl.
Rub in 1/4 cup lard, with fingers until evenly mixed.
Gradually stir in enough water to make soft dough.
Divide dough into quarters, making 12 pieces of soft dough in all.
Shape each into a small ball, with your hands.
Preheat griddle over medium heat and grease lightly.
Shape each ball into a flat round patty.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out each to an 8-inch circle.
Cook until bubbles form on top.
Turn tortillas down until underside is flecked with brown.
Makes 12 tortillas.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Based on the amount of sauce you need, add more of the ingredients.

title: toffee
directions: Butter square 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Spread pecans in pan. Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring constantly, for 7 minutes. Immediately spread mixture over nuts in pan. Sprinkle chocolate pieces over hot mixture so that contained heat will melt chocolate. Spread melted chocolate over candy. Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares. Chill until firm. (3 dozen candies.)

title: pan-fried scallops
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper and paprika; roll scallops thoroughly in bread crumb mixture.
In a large skillet, heat butter until frothy.
Add scallops and saute until lightly browned.
Gently remove scallops from skillet and arrange on bed of rice.
Add wine to butter in skillet; boil gently, while stirring, for 1 minute.
Pour over scallops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 1 1/2 pint strawberries in baked pie shell. Cook filling until it thickens. Remove from heat; stir in 1 small package strawberry jello. Cool, then pour in pie shell. Put in refrigerator to set. Serve with whipped topping.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: In a 2-cup measuring cup, combine the milk and the vinegar; mix well and set aside.
Cream together the Crisco, sugar and eggs. Stir 1 teaspoon baking soda into soured milk.
It will double in volume.
Mix together the salt, vanilla and rest of baking soda and the flour.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to the egg batter.
It will be stiff.
Roll out.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost, if desired, after cooled.

title: easy pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients according to can directions for pie. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin.
Melt butter and pour over the top, then sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cut into squares when cool and top with ice cream or Cool Whip.
This makes a delicious change from pumpkin pie!

title: quick vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables. Gently blend into the salad. Serve immediately. Yields 8 servings.

title: superb meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: If possible, put vegetables through blender or grinder.
If not, dice them very fine. The amount of vegetables will equal about 1 cup.
Combine with ground beef, tomato juice and seasonings; pack into pan (glass is best) and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Immediately pour off all liquid. Cool meat loaf slightly before slicing.
Serves 2 for dinner. This is the best meat loaf you've ever tasted.
Good cold, too.

title: ryan's mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Separate muffins.
Spread pizza sauce on top.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese and top with pepperoni slices. Bake on cookie sheet about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove chicken and save your broth.
Remove skin and bones and return to your broth.
Broth should be about 4 quarts.
Fry out streak of lean until crisp.
Let drain on paper towels.
In drippings, fry out onion, garlic, bell pepper, ham and capers.
Add olives and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add this to your broth and chicken.
Add rice.
Simmer until your liquid is gone and rice is done.

title: casserole bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water.
Let soften and stir. Add sugar, salt, butter, 1/2 cup cheese, oregano and 3 cups flour.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Beat at medium speed about 2 minutes. Beat in rest of flour with wooden spoon. Cover bowl with wax paper and towel and let rise in warm place (85°). I place bowl in sink with hot tap water.
This speeds up rising action until light and bubbly, double in size.
Lightly grease 2-quart casserole. Stir down batter and beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Turn in casserole. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Combine ground beef, spaghetti sauce, salt and water.
In 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish layer:
1/3 sauce, 1/2 uncooked lasagna noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat again, ending with sauce.
(Be sure noodles are covered completely with sauce.)
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave for 30 minutes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes before uncovering.

title: curried shrimp
directions: In large nonstick saucepan, heat the oil.
Add the pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring as needed until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add the flour, curry, ginger and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
Add the broth; cook stirring constantly until the mixture comes to a boil and thickens, about 2 minutes.
Add the shrimp and cook, stirring as needed until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serve the rice topped with shrimp mixture.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Add mayonnaise to flour and mix with spoon. Add milk, one cup at a time, until flour is like paste.
Spoon onto shallow pan or muffin pan. Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
(You can use extra flour after you make your paste so the biscuits can be rolled out.)

title: maple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on top of stove, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into pie shell and cover with crust. Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: west virginia mountain cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let stand to prepare rest of mixture.
Beat eggs separately.
Add and beat in oil, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts to apple/sugar mixture and add to mixture of eggs and flour, etc.
Pour into a greased and floured long or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a clean glass jar. Stir gently. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 3 weeks, stirring twice a week. Serve over pound cake, ice cream, etc., always reserving at least 1 cup of starter.

title: bacon-topped cheese potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub skins with vegetable oil. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done. Allow potatoes to cool to touch. Cut a 1-inch lengthwise strip

from top of each potato; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact. Combine potato pulp and remaining ingredients except bacon in a medium mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy; stuff shells with potato mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; top with crumbled bacon. Serve hot. Yield: 4 servings.

title: country cooking biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in shortening. Add
egg and milk.
Mix until dough forms.
Roll out and cut 3/4-inch
thick.
Place
on
ungreased
baking
sheet and freeze. When
frozen
store
in
plastic bag.
To bake, place biscuits on lightly greased baking pan and bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in Crisco until it looks like coarse meal.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to dry ingredients gently.
Pour in buttermilk and work to a nice dough. Roll out about 1/4 inch on a floured board and cut with biscuit cutters.
Dip in melted butter and place in pans, arranging biscuits as Parker House rolls.
Freeze and bake directly from the freezer at 400° for 15 minutes.
(Need not rise.)

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces and line casserole dish.
Put broccoli over chicken.
Pour uncooked rice over broccoli.
Heat Cheez Whiz, soup and broth until smooth.
Pour over chicken, rice and broccoli.
Heat in oven until bubbling hot for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, salt and cocoa. Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Add nuts and flavors.
Add flour last.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Do not bake too long.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spread rice in pan; place chicken over rice, skin side up.
Mix orange juice, sherry and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove cover last 1/2 hour of baking to brown.

title: doris' chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook noodles in broth and drain. Mix mushroom soup, sour cream with noodles and chicken.
Put in casserole. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Melt margarine and pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: berry tapioca salad
directions: Boil water and salt.
Add tapioca and cook slowly for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add sugar and jello.
Stir well.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, add berries and Cool Whip.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Put everything in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: "crumpton cornbread"
directions: Mix all
ingredients well and pour in heated muffin pan greased with
teaspoon Crisco corn oil.
Fill each muffin cup 2/3
full.	Bake
at
450° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 large muffins.

title: monkey bread
directions: Blend cinnamon and sugar in bowl.
Add biscuits and nuts.
Mix well.
Lightly grease Bundt pan and dump all in the pan.
Pour melted butter over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean dish
directions: Cook brown rice in microwave with 2 cups water plus 1 tablespoon.
Heat 8 to 10 minutes or until boiling on full power. Heat at power level 3 for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into small pieces (cut stems small). In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; mix well. Add to broccoli, raisins and onion; toss.
Add peanuts just before serving.
Crumble bacon over top.

title: string bean delight
directions: Cook beans with garlic; drain.
Mix beans and sour cream and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt butter and add bread crumbs. Mix well.
Sprinkle over beans and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.

title: pineapple crunch pie
directions: Divide pastry in half. Roll one portion on floured surface to a circle 1 1/2 inch larger than inverted 8 inch pie pan. Fit loosely into pan. Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and pineapple in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice and butter. Turn into pie shell.
Roll out remaining dough; cut slits. Moisten rim of bottom crust. Place top crust over filling. Fold edge under bottom crust, pressing to seal. Flute. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

Meanwhile, combine the brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and water in a saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Add chopped pecans. Spread hot mixture over top of partially-baked pie. Bake 9 to 12 minutes until deep golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken with pieces of celery in water.
Boil for 30 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Debone it, cube it and put in casserole.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.

title: granny's waldorf salad
directions: Dice apples and celery; add nuts.
Mix together the mayo, sugar and milk.
Add to the fruit.

title: gingerbread
directions: Blend together first seven ingredients and stir in boiling water.
Mix in unsifted flour.
Dissolve baking soda in 2 tablespoons of hot water; add to batter.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 1 pan (9 servings).
Approximate calories/serving:

title: southwestern stew
directions: Cut pork and sausage into bite size pieces.
In large pot, brown pork in oil for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Put pork back into pot and add sausage.
Stir chili powder and garlic into tomato sauce.
Pour over pork and sausage.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 10 minutes or until pork is tender.
After pork is done, stir in rice.
Turn off fire and let sit for 5 minutes. Serve with garlic toast prepared in Dutch oven or cornbread. Serves 4.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and salt.
Add the oil and vanilla.
Add pineapple with juice, mashed bananas, coconut and nuts.
Sift together the flour and soda, then add to other ingredients.
Pour into well floured and greased pans (makes 2 regular loaf pans).
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
(Can be frozen.)

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix ham with remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Place in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly.
Spray pan.
Put a layer of potatoes, a layer of onion, salt, pepper and margarine in pan until all ingredients are used.
Mix soup with milk and pour over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: mexican squash casserole
directions: Heat the sour cream, cheese, egg yolk, butter, salt and chives.
Combine all ingredients.
Top with dry bread crumbs, dots of butter and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: three-cheese pasta skillet
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Mix soup, water, pepper, cheeses and 2/3 cup onions in a skillet. Heat to a boil. Add pasta and top with remaining onions. Cover and cook over low heat for 2 minutes or until heated through.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until it thickens.
When thick, add jello.
Line the bottom of the pie shell with the peaches and pour the hot mixture over the top.
Chill until firm. Add Cool Whip on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: freda's chicken surprise
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat.
Take spatula or knife and spread cream cheese/chives mixture over chicken. Try to roll prepared chicken into jelly-roll style (cheese side out).
Wrap one slice of bacon around each breast half.
Place two toothpicks on ends to hold in place.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix sugar, lemon juice and vanilla with the hot water and Jell-O.
Let stand for a few minutes until cool.
Add cream cheese (softened).
Fold in whipped Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter and press into bottom of dish.
Save a few crumbs for topping.
Pour cheese cake mixture over the graham cracker crust. Garnish with remaining crumbs.

title: punch(tart)
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package, except use 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Mix in 9 cups Crispix and coat it well.
Put powdered sugar in a bag; add cereal a little at a time.
Shake to coat.
Lay on cookie sheet to dry.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy and stir in sugar replacement, water, flavoring and coloring.
Knead or work with hands until dough is smooth.

title: asparagus saute with butter and garlic
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter over high heat.
As soon as it foams, add the garlic and saute until it turns light golden, about 1 minute.
Add the asparagus and saute until it is tender-crisp and the garlic is nicely browned, 4 to 5 minutes. Serve immediately over cooked pasta.
Let each guest add a squeeze of lemon, salt and pepper to taste and plenty of Parmesan.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Grease 9 inch pie plate. Sprinkle broccoli, 1 c. cheese, the chicken and onion in pie plate. Stir baking mix, milk, eggs, salt and pepper with fork until blended. Pour into pie plate. Bake 32-37 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 1 to 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: six day stew(bachelors survival food)
directions: Braise stew beef in a 4 or 5-quart pot until well browned. Add canned vegetables with liquid.
Add stew starter.
Stir well!!!
Add mushrooms, bouillon cube, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Add water, salt and/or spices to taste.
Simmer slowly for 8 to 10 hours, stirring occasionally.
Let cool to room temperature.
Place covered pot in refrigerator for at least 24 hours to let flavors blend.
Place one serving in bowl and microwave until hot.
Enjoy!!!!!!
Will last for six days until gone, then you can make another pot.

title: olga's icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.

title: fruit and nut tropical slaw
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
Cut up pineapple; set aside.
Combine the reserved pineapple syrup and lemon juice.
Coat banana slices with 1 tablespoon of the juice mixture; set remaining juice aside.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake as shown on box.
Make pudding as shown on box. Crumble cake up and start layering.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O together.
Add milk, pie filling and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Salad tastes better if left to set overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and shred potatoes on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat chicken soup, sour cream, cheese and butter and pour over potatoes.
Combine melted butter and corn flakes and pour over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix ingredients 50 to 75 strokes until moistened.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Stem and thoroughly crush strawberries, one layer at a time. Measure 2 1/4 cups into 6 or 8-quart saucepot.
Finely chop rhubarb; do not peel.
Place in 2-quart saucepan; add 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 minutes or until rhubarb is soft.
Measure 1 3/4 cups; add to saucepot. Prepare jars.
Keep jars and lids hot until ready to fill. Measure sugar into separate bowl.
Stir pectin into fruit in saucepot.
Add margarine.
Place over heat; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Immediately stir in all sugar. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon. Ladle quickly into prepared jars, filling to within 1/8-inch of tops.
Wipe jar rims and threads.
Cover with two-piece lids. Screw bands tightly.
Invert jars for 5 minutes, then turn upright.
After jars cool, check seals.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients 10 minutes on medium speed.

title: canned bean soup (from dry beans)
directions: In pot, put beans, salt and fill with water.
Ham or bacon can be added as desired.
Process in canner for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: banana praline muffins
directions: In a small bowl, stir together brown sugar and sour cream. Stir in pecans.
Set it aside.
Mash bananas.
In another bowl, stir together egg, sugar, oil and mashed bananas until well blended.
Add sour cream mixture.
Add pancake mix, stirring just until moistened.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with assorted fruit.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Put in 13 x 9-inch pan in order as listed.
Bake at 350° or 325° for glass dish.

title: spinach, red pepper and feta quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake a prepared pie crust according to directions.
(I use the ready crust in the red box.) While the shell is baking, saute the bell pepper in a large skillet in oil over moderately high heat, stirring, for a couple of minutes.
Add spinach and saute, stirring, until wilted and tender, a few minutes.
Remove skillet from heat and season spinach lightly.
In a small bowl, whisk together eggs and cream.
Sprinkle Feta over the bottom of the baked pie shell and arrange spinach mixture on top.
Pour cream mixture over spinach and bake quiche on a baking sheet in the middle of oven 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake until set, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: two-cheese shrimp tarts
directions: For Pastry:
In a small mixing bowl, let semi-soft cheese or cream cheese and margarine or butter soften at room temperature. Stir together.
Stir in flour. Divide into 12 pieces.
Place one piece in the center of a seasoned 2 1/2-inch sandbakkelser mold. Press pastry evenly and thinly over bottom and up sides of mold. Repeat with remaining pastry.
Place molds on jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Cool.
Using a toothpick, carefully put in an airtight container.
(Or return pastry shells to jelly roll pan and cover with foil.)
Seal, label and freeze for up to 2 months.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, stir all dry ingredients.
In another bowl, mix together all liquid ingredients.
Pour liquid ingredients into middle of dry ingredients.
Stir with a fork, scraping sides and corners of pan, until the mixture is uniform in color.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in the pan before cutting.

title: parmesan meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, 1/2 cup of the spaghetti sauce, crackers, 1/2 cup of the cheese, onion and egg.
Shape into loaf in a 12 x 8 baking dish.
Top with remaining spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or to desired doneness.

title: foolproof macaroni and cheese
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Melt margarine in oven in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in macaroni and stir well, coating macaroni with melted margarine.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour milk over all; stir.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Do not stir while baking.

title: crescent roll chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and butter in medium bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 squares, rather than 8 triangles.
Flatten dough and pinch seams together.
Divide the chicken mixture into equal portions and scoop onto the middle of the roll.
Pull dough around the chicken and press the dough together.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until rolls are done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg; add vanilla and molasses.
Sift flour and soda.
Mix well and add raisins, oatmeal and walnuts. Make into balls and gently pat down.
Bake at 350°.

title: sort of vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the first 5 ingredients until tender.
Add soups, water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, zucchini, green beans and salt.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 7 layer cookie
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 11 pan; sprinkle and press cracker crumbs over margarine. Spread coconut, chips and nuts. Cover with Eagle Brand milk. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: woodman's stew
directions: Prepare and cook stew as directed on package, using ingredients, about as listed, except peas.
Add peas last 10 minutes of cooking.
Serves 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
Let cake cool.
Divide cake in thirds.
Crumble up cake.

title: pork roast with dressing
directions: Bake or cook roast until done.
Retain juices.
Place in baking dish.
Crush crackers in mixing bowl.
Add egg, pepper and enough juice to make mixture consistency which will stick to roast.
Cover roast with mixture and bake until brown.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy; add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Frost with following recipe for glaze.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add eggs, water and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking soda together and add to sugar mixture.
Add cereals and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon
on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches to have 6 cups.
Arrange in the pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over peaches. Top with the second crust and seal edges well.
Poke top and bake 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mounds
directions: Combine all ingredients except wax and chocolate chips. Chill. Shape into small balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate and enough wax to form a smooth coating. Dip balls in chocolate mixture and set aside on wax paper.
Store in an airtight container.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Don't stir after boiling begins!
Remove from heat and add the next four ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chipped ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Place in hamburger buns and wrap in foil. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: penuche(brown sugar fudge)
directions: Step 1:
Line an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil; set pan aside.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese with salt.
Add pineapple, 1 cup of nuts, peppers and onion.
Chill mixture well, then shape into ball.
Roll in 1 cup of nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: In a heavy pot, saute pepper, celery and onion in margarine until onion is transparent.
Add chicken broth and potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Make a thin white sauce with margarine, flour and milk; slowly add to soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: special sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make small balls.
Roll tops in white sugar, colored sugars or sprinkles.
Press in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until edges are light brown.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together about 2 to 4 minutes.
Put in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar; add pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and place in fridge. Mix pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and butter; put in microwave three minutes. Stir well when cool. Mix the two mixtures together and place in fridge until ready to eat.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice. Beat on low until mixture is crumbly. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Slice apples into lemon juice (or other citrus fruit juice) to keep from discoloration.
Drain and serve apples with dip.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan.
Line with wax paper.
Butter again. Sift flour and soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, nuts and fruit. Fold in dry ingredients; pour into pan.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 hours; cool.
Turn out of pan.
Remove wax paper and decorate as you like.

title: cheesy eggplant sticks
directions: Peel and quarter eggplant lengthwise. If using regular eggplant, cut into smaller wedges. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Mix butter, onion and garlic. Brush mixture on eggplant sticks. Broil eggplant about 5 to 7 minutes. Turn. Brush with butter. Broil 5 minutes longer. Sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: scandinavian cucumbers
directions: Stir together sour cream, parsley, tarragon vinegar, sugar and chives.
Fold in cucumbers.
Cover and chill.

title: ethel's brown rice
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Cover; bake about 1 hour.

title: reuben bake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cook noodles and drain.
Toss with 2 tablespoons
oleo.
Place noodles in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Top with sauerkraut and shredded corned beef.
Spread
dressing
over
corned beef and top with tomato slices.
Sprinkle
with
Swiss
cheese.
Toss
cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons butter or oleo and caraway seed and sprinkle over top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: nora's hot taco rice(serves 3)
directions: Brown beef with onions; wash off with warm water.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube; boil 5 minutes, then simmer.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Saute onion and hot dogs in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Shred cabbage and add to onion and hot dogs.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add to onion, hot dogs and cabbage. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with sugar; dissolve with water.
Add lemonade (with water added as directed on can).
Add pineapple juice. Freeze in Ziploc bags.
Thaw about 4 hours before serving.
Mix ginger ale with slushy mixture when ready to serve.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray. Place cheese slices on top of chicken.
Spread soup over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle croutons and oregano on top of soup.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.

title: hide the meat
directions: In a heavy skillet brown hamburger lightly and remove fat. Chop celery, carrots, pepper, onion and canned tomatoes.
Add all ingredients to hamburger except cheese and V-8.
Saute until onions appear transparent.
Stir in V-8 juice.
Cover and steam for 3 to 5 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Cover.
Allow cheese to melt.
Serve.

title: tomato skillet cabbage
directions: Drain tomato juice and reserve.
In medium skillet, heat tomato liquid and bouillon until it dissolves.
Stir in cabbage. Cover tightly.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes.
Cover, cook until cabbage is crisp-tender and tomatoes are heated through, about 3 to 5 minutes (45 calories each serving).
Serves 4.

title: honey chicken breast
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter; drain.
Add all ingredients. Place in a Pyrex baking dish.
Bake covered for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Alternately fold in crumbs and milk.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Batter may appear curdled.
Spoon into 9-inch tube pan which has been greased, floured and lined on bottom with waxed paper. Evenly spread batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and remove wax paper.
Finish cooling on rack.
Frost or glaze as desired.

title: rosenmunnar "red lips"
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Cream butter and sugar to a fluffy consistency.
Add flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into olive size balls.
Arrange on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press small well in center of each cookie with tip of handle of wooden spoon.
Fill center with jelly or jam.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until delicately brown on edges.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: michigan-style vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with corn chips, vegetables or crackers.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients for filling. Spread pecans in bottom of pie shell then pour mixture on top of pecans. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 - 35 minutes longer. When pie is done the outer edges of filling should be set and center slightly soft.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Mix ingredients and melt in crock pot on low.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over milk.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Place in blender with pineapple and corn syrup; cover.
Blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover; freeze overnight.
Soften slightly at room temperature, about 15 minutes.
Spoon into large bowl.
With mixer at low speed, beat until smooth, but not melted.
Pour into 4-cup mold or freezer container.
Cover; freeze about 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold or soften at room temperature for easier scooping.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with liquid smoke, garlic powder, onion salt and celery salt. Allow to stand overnight covered with foil. Next morning, sprinkle with pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and bake 5 hours at 275°. Drain grease off then. Uncover and bake 1 hour with Barbecue Sauce.

title: crispy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients to have a thin consistency; soupy mixture. Set mixture aside.
Heat iron corn bread skillet, greasing skillet with extra bacon drippings.
Pour some of the mixture into skillet and cook on medium-low heat.
Turn bread when it bubbles and the edges turn brown.

title: frozen mock margaritas
directions: Place limeade, lemonade, powdered sugar and egg whites in blender.
Blend until smooth and frothy.
Add cracked ice gradually to thicken. Add enough club soda to cut tartness to your taste.
Pour into prepared chilled glasses (rimmed with salt, if desired). This is done by going around the top of the glass with a lime wedge and then dipping the rim into a plate of coarse salt to coat.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Drain water chestnuts and slice.
Chop celery.
Combine chicken, water chestnuts, celery and peas.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Add to chicken.
Toss well.
Chill for several hours.
Serve on bibb or fresh lettuce.

title: best ever nachos
directions: Spray a 3-quart deep casserole dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Melt butter in casserole; add garlic and saute until golden brown.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add chiles, tomato and cilantro, if wanted, and simmer until tender.
Add refried beans, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese; cook over low heat until cheese melts and mixture is boiling.
Stir often.
Cool.
Cover and chill well.

title: dilly dip for vegies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with vegetables, cut for dipping.
Yields 3 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to slow oven (300°) and bake about 1 hour.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, chocolate, syrup and salt in covered pan on low heat until soft ball stage (cook slowly).
Cool until lukewarm, covered and without stirring.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat with electric beater at high speed until thick.
Add nuts. Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch or bread pan.
Cool and cut.

title: flank steak
directions: Combine steak, onion quarters and water in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for one hour or until meat is tender.
Drain; reserve 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Cool.
Shred meat or cut into small pieces; set aside.
Cook peppers, onion strips and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet for 3 minutes. Stir in meat and reserved liquid (1 1/2 cups).
Cook 10 minutes. Add peas.
Remove bay leaves.
Stir well and cook 10 minutes. Toast garlic bread and serve with meat mixture.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Dice raw bacon and cook in skillet until golden brown.
Drain grease.
Prepare onions, green pepper and eggs, then add bacon to cooked potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Serve warm.
Serves 25.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil, sugar and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Stir in soda, cream of tartar, salt and flour.
Roll teaspoon of dough into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Press down on lightly greased cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and knead 5 minutes.
Shape into 5 rolls and wrap in foil. Refrigerate 2 to 4 days.
Remove foil and put on wire racks with drip pan underneath and bake 9 hours at 160°.
Rewrap in foil and freeze or refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients. Fold in 8 or 12 ounces Cool Whip and chill.

title: violet's french split pea soup
directions: Soak green split peas overnight in water.
Saute onions in oil and set aside.
Cook ham for 30 minutes.
Combine ham and onions to make broth.
Add peas to broth and simmer until peas are soft and mushy (approximately 1 hour).
The last 5 minutes add a cup of shredded American cheese and salt.
Thin this thick mixture with milk or water before serving.
Can be stored or frozen.

title: holiday cranberry relish
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Heat to boiling over medium heat.
Add cranberries.
Reduce heat; cook until skin pops.
Remove from heat.
Let cool to room temperature, then add the rest of ingredients and chill.

title: sausage spaghetti primavera
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain. In large skillet, heat oil.
Add sausage and remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Cook and stir over medium heat just until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Toss together hot spaghetti, sausage mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: pasghetti pizza
directions: Combine eggs, milk, 1 cup Mozzarella, garlic powder, salt and cooked spaghetti. Blend well.
Spread into 15 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pasta dijon salad
directions: In large bowl combine mustard, oil, vinegar, scallions, garlic and tomato.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss lately.
Serve immediately.

title: burritos
directions: Combine Filling ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Place filling in tortillas and roll. Top with cheese and lettuce.

title: caramel pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk; fold in whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 mixture in crust.
Drizzle with half of caramel topping. Combine coconut and pecans; sprinkle half over the caramel. Repeat layers.
Chill or freeze until serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add powdered sugar until desired consistency.
If it gets too thick, add milk.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Lay chicken (or other meat of your choice) in bottom of dish. Pour soup and
broth
over chicken. Add rice on top and butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ann's clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese (room temperature) with clams, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Add juice until it is in dipping consistency. Better after a couple of hours in the refrigerator.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Into 2 gallons of water, add sausage, potatoes, onions, lemons, seafood seasoning, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 45 minutes.
Add butter and melt.
Add corn and cook for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 4 minutes or until pink. Drain water.
Serve on large platter.
Serves 12.

title: papaya salsa
directions: In a small nonstick saucepan, heat the oil and saute the shallots and ginger over medium heat for 6 to 7 minutes, until softened, stirring often.
Remove the pan from heat and stir in the curry powder until well blended.
Add the remaining ingredients, place in a covered container and chill for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Serve chilled.
Yields 1 cup.

title: swedish pound cake
directions: Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Eggs one at a time.
Sift in flour, salt and flavorings.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add molasses, then hot water with soda.
Then add dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Roll, cut and place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: refrigerated rolls
directions: Combine shortening and scalded milk.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar and salt and beat in cold water.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water and combine the three mixtures.
Add the flour and knead until smooth.
Cover tight and refrigerate overnight.
Shape as standard rolls and let rise in warm place.
Bake at 375°.
Keep remainder of dough covered tight and refrigerated.
Dough will keep 5 or so days.

title: peanut butter 'n chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars and peanut butter in large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets.

title: sweet fruit slaw
directions: Put shredded cabbage into large bowl.
Stir apple, oranges, grapes and raisins or nuts into cabbage.
Cover and chill.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in microwave for 1.5 minutes. Add sugar, flour, vanilla, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a 10-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican rub
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container. Sprinkle on chicken, ribs or fish before grilling or baking. Makes 1/2 cup.
May double.
(Low heat.)

title: four star spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal into 2 cups of the milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add remaining milk, butter and eggs.
Put in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Combine nuts, sugar and butter in skillet and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 6 to 8 minutes or until sugar is melted and nuts are toasted. Spread nuts on buttered baking sheet. Separate or put in clusters. Cool, then eat.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well and form into meat balls.
Bake in oven on broiler pan so grease drips away.
Bake at 325° until done (cut 1 open to see if center is cooked), about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and freeze or serve with tomato sauce over rice or noodles.

title: holiday shrimp aspic
directions: Heat soup to boiling; remove from stove.
Add cheese or sour cream.
Beat until blended.
Meanwhile, soak gelatin in cold water, 5 minutes.
Add to hot soup mixture, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool, not thicken.
Stir in all remaining ingredients. Pour into mold.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: dill pickles(kosher style)
directions: Wash and rinse six 32 ounce jars and their closures.
Keep jars and closures immersed in separate kettles of hot water until you are to use.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown and drain beef; add sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Grease large pan.
Use 1/2 sauce on bottom of pan; layer with noodles, cottage cheese,
Mozzarella and meat sauce.
Repeat layers until mix is all used.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: crab dip mold
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add to warm soup. Cool slightly. Combine with all the other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into mold (either ring tip or maybe a fish shaped one). Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: dream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in bowl until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: hair stimulant
directions: Mix and use on hair and scalp each night.
Taken from a medical book with a copyright date of 1911.
Writer claims this treatment stopped her hair from coming out.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil in saucepan and heat until sugar melts.
Mix beans and onions; add the heated liquids and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Better the longer it stands; will keep for a week in the refrigerator.

title: spicy meat balls in milk gravy
directions: Mix together meat, potatoes and seasonings.
Shape into 16 balls.
Roll each in flour to cover well.
Brown slowly in hot margarine in heavy skillet.
Pour off fat drippings.
Add water; cover and cook for 1/2 hour slowly.
Add more water, if necessary to prevent sticking.
Add milk mixture with 1 tablespoon flour. Cook long enough for gravy to thicken slightly.
Season to taste. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter and cheese. Add milk.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: In small bowl, mix flour and salt.
Add shortening and cut into flour until mixture forms pea sized balls.
Add water and mix with a fork until the dough forms a ball.
Roll out on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
If rolled very thin, makes enough for 1 (9 or 10-inch) pie shell or an 8-inch two crust pie.
Line pie pan with rolled out dough and set aside.

title: cousin maddy's lemon pie
directions: Mix all wet ingredients.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook pie crust until golden brown.
Add mixture and bake for 20 minutes. Turn oven off and cook for another 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: green salad
directions: Melt jello with 1/2 cup hot water. Add remaining ingredients, then chill until congealed.

title: chicken casserole for a crowd(serves 12 to 15)
directions: To serve, pour sauce over squares of the casserole.

title: tuna stuffed tomatoes
directions: In a mixing bowl, flake tuna and combine with beans, corn, cheese, dressing and onion. Cover and chill for an hour. Core tomatoes and carefully take out part of the center, making a shallow bowl. Drain tomatoes upside down on a paper towel. Cut each tomato in 5 to 6 wedges almost to the bottom, but leaving intact. Gently open each tomato and fill with tuna mixture. Serve with favorite cracker or chips, pickles and/or lettuce wedges.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Put all ingredients, except crackers and oleo in casserole dish.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs and melted oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Pat cutlets dry with paper towels.
Dip in dressing crumbs and set aside for a few minutes on wax paper.
Dip in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Fry in 1/4-inch of oil until browned.
Place cutlets in casserole.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, zucchini, squash, carrots, red pepper, eggplant and garlic cloves in olive oil for about 1 to 2 minutes only.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 1 hour.
Add grated cheese to taste.

title: the preacher's chicken
directions: Combine salt and pepper; sprinkle chicken cavity with the mixture.
Peel onion and potatoes, then quarter them.
Melt butter with vegetable oil in large casserole or Dutch oven.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Combine boiling water and chicken bouillon cubes in 1-cup measure, stirring until dissolved.
Add to casserole with chicken.
Place onion and potatoes around chicken; sprinkle with basil and rest of salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 325°, basting once or twice, for 1 1/4 hours, until vegetables are tender.

title: rice 'n sausage casserole
directions: Whack the sausage in small bits.
Lightly brown hit in skillet.
Stir often.
Add watah.
Combine othah ingredients ('ceptin' buttah) 'n stir into hog meat.
Dump into a greased casserole.
Dot wid buttah 'n bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: italian chicken
directions: Prepare chicken by peeling off the skin and rinsing with water.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: vagabond beans
directions: Chop raisins, onion and apple fine.
Combine all ingredients; turn into bean pot or casserole.
Bake, covered, in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; slowly stir in slightly cooled milk and vanilla.
Fill six 5 ounce custard cups.
Set in shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water into pan 1 inch deep.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix beef and vegetables in heavy pan or skillet with tight fitting lid.
Sprinkle over top of mixture, tapioca, salt, sugar, pepper and pour V-8 juice over mixture.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Don't peek!
Can use 13 x 9-inch cake pan and cover with foil.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add heavy cream to chocolate to a smooth consistency.
Add Grand Marnier to taste.
Serve with fruit or pound cake.
Serves 20 people.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients with mixer.
Then add shrimp. (Flake out of can with fork.
Mix in with spoon, not mixer.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Do not use electric mixer.
Use large spoon or wooden spoon. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add apples and nuts.
Combine sugar and eggs; add oil and mix.
Add this apple mixture.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan and bake at 350° for one hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.
Top with Lemon Glaze.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, cocoa and margarine. Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and nuts. Beat with mixer and spread on cake while hot.

title: banana cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Make a well and add oil and eggs.
Mix well by hand.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
This can also be made in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and baked for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix all together (except chocolate chips)
in a large bowl.
Press evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and softened margarine, then mix slightly beaten eggs, meal, vinegar and vanilla.
Add to sugar and margarine. Bake in uncooked pie shell at 300° until firm.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add oil to pot with garlic and onions and saute on medium heat.
(If fresh beans are used, saute with onions and garlic.) Add boiling water and bouillon, then frozen vegetables.
Add zucchini and squash last.
Let simmer for 10 minutes and serve. Serves 6.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Separately mix milk, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Beat egg and oil together, adding to milk and yeast mixtures (all together).
Add flour and beat well (do not knead).
Place dough in large, greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover with damp cloth.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: frosting(good on german chocolate cake)
directions: Mix together; frost cooled cake.

title: chicken or turkey bundles
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk, dill, salt and pepper until smooth. Stir in meat, celery and onions. Unroll dough and separate into 12 rectangles (4 from each tube). Place on greased baking sheet and press the perforations together.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into the center of each rectangle.
Bring edges up to the center and pinch to seal. Brush with butter; sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden. Serves 6.

title: strawberry meringue bars
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour; stir until blended.
Spread mixture into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread evenly with preserves.
Beat egg whites; beat in sugar gradually.
Fold in nutmeats.
Spread meringue carefully over preserves.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Makes 18 bars.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soup and broth.
Stir in cheese and mix with turkey, pasta and mushrooms.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: granny gage's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars and vanilla pudding until smooth.
Add eggs, then flour and soda.
Mix oats; drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain thoroughly; mix all ingredients together.
Use with pumpernickel bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with butter.
Spread half in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and 1 cup broth; pour over stuffing.
Sprinkle remainder of stuffing over top and then pour remainder of broth over top.
Cook at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: l. a.'s party punch
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together.
Then add the ginger ale.
Serve chilled or float ice sculptures in punch bowl.

title: herb spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
