Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 6.
May be prepared ahead and baked later.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil water and turn off. Melt butter in a 13 x 9 pan. Mix together next 5 ingredients and pour over melted butter. Stir together 1 1/2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Sift over top of other. Take boiling water and pour over all ingredients. Bake 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn(yields 4 servings)
directions: In a big saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook together until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda (it will "erupt").
Pour mixture over popcorn in vegetable oil sprayed pan.
(Use turkey roaster top and bottom if you have one.)
Cook for 1 hour at 200° (stir every 15 minutes). Remove and dump on wax paper.

title: dill pickles
directions: Take cucumbers, salt, vinegar and water.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Add garlic.
Bring water and salt to boiling point.
Add vinegar and let boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Add dill to top of jars and seal.

title: indian punch cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep base refrigerated.
Add equal amount of ginger ale (about two 2 liter bottles) and lots of ice in punch bowl.

title: hole-in-the-middle
directions: Spray electric skillet (or skillet) with nonstick cooking spray.
Preheat to 325° to 350°.
Using a glass, make a round hole in the bread slices.
Lightly spread each circle of bread on both sides with margarine.
Place cut out bread in skillet and place 1 to 2 teaspoons margarine in each hole.
When melted, break an egg in each hole.
Place bread circles in skillet.
Fry eggs as you like them, turning once.
Turn bread circles once to brown on the other side.
Serve immediately.

title: creamy peanut butter fruit dip
directions: In a medium bowl combine milk, sour cream, and pudding mix. Whisk until smooth.
Add peanut butter and sugar.
Whisk until well blended.
Serve with fruit slices.
Apples and bananas work well. May refrigerate until needed.
Yields 12 (1/4 c.) servings

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening in hot water.
Add sugar, yeast, egg and enough flour to make rolls.
Pinch off and make small rolls. Place in warm area and cover.
Let rise approximately 1/2 to 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheddar vegetable squares
directions: Chop onion.
In large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion; cover and cook until tender.
Add vegetables, marjoram, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Heat until smooth the Velveeta cheese, milk and Miracle Whip. Add to the first mixture the chicken, noodles and broccoli.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Shake well.
Pour over meat and let sit overnight.
Refrigerate remaining marinade.

title: mushroom orzo pilaf
directions: In a large skillet saute onion in butter until tender.
Add orzo, brown it a little bit.
Stir constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until orzo is tender.
All liquid must be absorbed. When done sprinkle with cut parsley.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Mix mustard, flour,
salt
and	sugar well.
Heat cider vinegar to boiling.
Pour slowly over the dry mix and stir out lumps.
Put in covered container and close tightly.
Age about 5 days before using.

title: ranch cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk and eggs, mixing well. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients
together well.
Store in a tightly closed container.
To mix with boiling water, use 2 teaspoons of tea mixture per cup.

title: clam fondue
directions: Melt cheese.
Add all other ingredients and put into fondue pot, keeping warm while serving.
Serve with bread cubes.

title: mama's custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat very well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Heat butter or bacon fat in skillet; add meat and stir until very lightly browned.
Add onion, water, tomatoes and salt; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add peas with their liquid and cooked noodles and cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, 10 or 15 minutes longer, or until as much liquid as desired has evaporated.
Add more seasonings if desired and serve hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat well at high speed on mixer about 4 minutes.
Add salt, vanilla, syrup and pecans.
Beat well at high speed on mixer about 4 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for an additional 40 minutes or until pie is golden brown and feels firm when touched.

title: mom's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast and 1/2 cup sugar together and cover with plastic wrap for 20 minutes.
Mix eggs, salt, 1 cup sugar, food coloring and Crisco.
Add this to yeast mixture and stir together to mix.
Stir flour into mixture, a little at a time.
Spray with Pam.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours until double in size.
Roll out on floured counter.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Then add brown sugar, raisins, nuts, etc.
Roll up and cut into rolls. Place (6 only) rolls in each 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise again double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 48 rolls.
Top with powdered sugar icing.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut around core of cabbage.
Put in pan of boiling water and wilt.
Take leaves apart; cut thick part off leaves.
Mix the filling and fill leaves.
Fold over and pin with toothpicks.
Put 1 big can tomato juice in heavy saucepan and let come to a boil. Add leaves and simmer 1 hour.
Add 1 can of tomato sauce.
Simmer until thick.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and milk until smooth.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add butter and spices.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 425 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook all of above ingredients slowly for 2 - 4 hours.

title: super easy dessert
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put brown sugar and boiling water. Stir well. Add crushed pineapple, then sprinkle dry cake mix over top of sugar and pineapple mixture (do not stir). Slice the 1/4 pound margarine over top of this mixture, then sprinkle coconut and finally chopped nuts over top of complete mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes. Serve warm with scoop of vanilla ice cream or cold with whipped cream or plain. Serves 12.

title: empress chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings; discard tips.
Combine soy sauce, minced ginger and garlic in large bowl.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken. Reserve marinade.

title: breakfast wassail
directions: Combine all juices and bring to a boil.
Add water.
Serve hot or cold.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture after each egg.
Beat well.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Pour in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: magic out of a lump of coal
directions: In a glass or plastic bowl, put pieces of coal, coke, porous brick, tile, small pieces of broken cement or sponge.
To prevent staining, place bowl on a protected surface.
Mix together 2 tablespoons water, 2 tablespoons table salt and 2 tablespoons liquid bluing, then pour this over the coal or other contents of the bowl; let stand overnight.
Next morning, sprinkle 2 more tablespoons salt over the base.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl, mixing well.
In a saucepan, put margarine, shortening, cocoa and water and bring to a rapid boil and then pour over flour and sugar, mixing gradually. Put soda in buttermilk and add with other ingredients.
Mix and turn into a greased and floured pan, about 11 x 16-inches.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: three bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Mix well. Pour over vegetables and toss. Cover and chill at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook until slightly thickened. Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Pour into freezer can.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Fill can with milk.
You can add 2 to 3 cups of your favorite fruit, if desired.
Freeze until firm.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done when knife is inserted at 400°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and margarine.
Beat in sugar. Add 2 eggs and 1 cup of flour alternately.
Blend in vanilla. Bake in greased Bundt pan.

title: egg custard
directions: Separate eggs.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of sugar to add to beaten egg whites.
Warm the milk, having just tepid.
Mix flour with dry sugar.
Beat egg yolks, add sugar and flour.
Add melted butter, then milk and flavorings.
Beat egg whites stiff; add reserved sugar as making meringue.
Fold into the mixture.
Pour in partly baked pie shell (deep shell).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and freeze overnight until firm slush. (Ice cream bucket great to freeze in.)
Spoon into punch bowl, then add ginger ale.

title: easy bake rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and half of the flour.
Blend for 2 to 3 minutes, scraping bowl.
Blend in remaining flour until smooth, scraping sides of bowl.
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Turn onto floured board or wax paper.
Use hand and press out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on greased pan or sheet.
(I use 2 large frying pans, sometimes 3, according to size you cut them.)
Let rise about 20 minutes.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: mama's fruit pudding
directions: Mix together.
Put fruit in greased casserole dish.
Pour dough on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chocolate.
Cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well.
Blend in sour cream and chocolate water.
Makes a thin batter.
Pour into greased waxed paper-lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out and remove paper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, half and half and mustard in a bowl.
Butter one side of white bread and place it in a 9 x 13-inch pan buttered side down.
Put cooked hash browns on top of bread.
Put cooked sausage on top of hash browns.
Put cheese on top of sausage. Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 1 hour.
Prepare the night before and bake in the
morning.

title: satin ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in water. Add to Cool Whip and milk.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker or vanilla wafer crusts. Makes 2 pies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni accordingly to package directions.
Drain and combine next 11 ingredients and toss well.
Chill at least one hour and spoon into lettuce leaves.
Arrange tomato slices and egg wedges around edges and garnish with parsley.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and sugar; set aside. Mix vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk and vanilla.
Crumble 1/2 of cookies in a pan or dish (9 x 13-inch).
Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture; add all of Cool Whip except enough to make a topping (use about 12 ounces).
Spread on cookies.
Crumble balance of cookies on pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip to cover cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.
Keep in refrigerator until ready for use.
This is equal to 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add vanilla, sugar and salt. Fold in 2 1/2 cups of pecans.
Place separate pecan halves on a cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 210°.
Leave on foil until cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown and drain bacon, hamburger meat and onion.

In a separate sauce pan, simmer together ketchup, dry mustard, vinegar and brown sugar. Mix meat mixture and sauce with remaining ingredients (beans). Place in casserole dish and bake for 40-60 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together the soup, water and sour cream.
Layer potatoes, butter, cheese and soup mixture.
Add seasoning.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Add milk; fill can with water.
Add 6 egg yolks (beaten).
Cook and stir constantly until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: chipped ham sandwich
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Then add the chipped ham and bake 30 minutes.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt
and sour cream in saucepan.

Add butter or margarine.
Let

Beat

Spread

buttered 8-inch square pan. When firm, cut into squares.
Makes about 24 pieces.
Nuts may be substituted with shredded or flaked coconut.
Or use puffed rice cereal in place of nuts.

title: laver-seafood soup(traditional)
directions: *Gather laver (seaweed) during low tides in May and early June.
Turn frequently until dry.
Chop and crumble.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and cook to soft ball (235°). Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Beat until starts to lose its gloss. Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: taco sauce dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Layer cream cheese mixture on a plate.
Add taco sauce, 4 ounces Cheddar cheese, chopped tomato and chopped pepper.
Then add remaining Cheddar cheese on top.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into pie shells and put in freezer for 4 to 6 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute butter and stuffing.
Spread half in casserole dish, mix other ingredients and spoon on top of stuffing mixture.
Then top with other half of stuffing mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix minus 1 cup, oleo, and egg.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake @ 400° for 10 min.
Mix together pumpkin, eggs, 1 tsp cinnamon, 3/4 cup sugar and 2/3 cup evaporated milk. Pour over crust.
Mix to a crumbly texture the 1 cup reserved dry cake mix, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tsp. cinnamon, 2 tbs melted oleo and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake @ 350° for 50 min.

title: cinnamon flop cake
directions: Break 1 egg into cup and fill with milk.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach.
Mix
with
onion,
soup and cheese.
Put into buttered 1 quart casserole dish.
Mix butter and stuffing mix and spread
over
mixture.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate fudge pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into the 2 pie crusts. Cook 10 minutes on 400° then cook 25 minutes on 300°.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: You will need foil cupcake liners.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Liquefy first 6 ingredients; when creamy, pour into double boiler.
Stir mixture with a wire whisk; when thickened, continue cooking over low heat until the arrowroot is thoroughly cooked. Add vanilla and bananas over low heat.
Pour custard into a baked pie crust or simply sprinkle some coconut on bottom of a pie plate and fill with custard.
Sprinkle small amount of coconut over top. Chill and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add the remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or longer, until hot.
Adjust spices to your own taste.

title: easy low-fat dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate until ready to use. Great dip for vegetables and chips.
Also good on baked potatoes instead of sour cream. A delicious salad dressing.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add milk and stir.
Fold in egg and oil.
Pour onto hot griddle, flipping when they start to bubble.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Blend butter and soups with milk.
Pour butter and soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice and pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Slice bananas on top of this mixture.
Then layer chopped nuts, coconut and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top for final layer and decorate with cherries.

title: rolled stuffed steak
directions: Mix box stuffing according to directions.
Stuff steak with stuffing and close with toothpicks.
Peel and quarter potatoes. Mix 1 envelope of onion soup and can of cream mushroom soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over steak and potatoes and bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: luby's shredded carrots
directions: Combine carrots, pineapple, mayonnaise, raisins and sugar. Chill until ready to serve.

title: quick potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Pour butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheeses and bake for 25 minutes at 475°. Serve hot.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: Combine egg, milk, vanilla, salt and milk.
Blend good. Gently blend in cream.
Pour into punch bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: grandma's lemon chiffon pie
directions: In double boiler (or microwave), cook egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring frequently, until consistency of thick custard.
Soak gelatine in cold water until dissolved.
Add to hot custard.
Let cool.
Beat 3 egg whites stiff, but not dry (so still glossy).
Beat in 1 cup sugar gradually.
Fold cooled custard into beaten egg whites.
Put into baked pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook on medium heat until thick (about 10 minutes).
Add salt, butter and then beets.
Cover and continue cooking, about 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add mayonnaise to consistency desired.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add margarine, soup and Mexicorn.
Mix well and put in a baking dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Place in oven long enough to melt cheese, then serve.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill before serving.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown onion and celery.
Add meat; brown and drain.
Add paste and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup cheese to meat mixture. Simmer together 5 minutes.
Separate crescent dough and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture onto crescent rolls.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: jimmy's rice pilaf
directions: Cook butter and onion until golden. Add rice until golden. Add rest of ingredients.
Let come to a boil, cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, salt and shortening together.
Mixture will be coarse.
Combine egg with vinegar and water; mix well.
Add to the flour mixture all at once.
Mix and shape into a ball. Divide into 3 or 4 dough balls.
Refrigerate until needed.
(Dough will keep for 3 weeks in the refrigerator or 3 months in the freezer compartment.)
Yields 3 or 4 pie crusts.

title: cheddar pig crackers
directions: Cut butter in pieces.
Combine with cheese in food processor. Add flour, salt and red pepper.
Pulse processor to form dough. Shape into flattened ball; wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: 57 rib glaze
directions: Combine 57 sauce and honey. Grill ribs, turning and brushing with glaze during the last 10 minutes of cooking time. Enjoy.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together the meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place in skillet.
Mix together the soup and water; pour over meatballs.
Cook over medium heat for approximately 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Crumble bacon and add to potato, celery and onion mixture; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 heaping tablespoon flour to bacon grease and stir until smooth.
Add 1/3 cup vinegar, 2/3 cup sugar and 1 cup water; cook and stir until smooth.
Add more of vinegar mixture if too thick.
Taste and add more sugar, water or vinegar to your taste if necessary.
Add to potato mixture and mix well. Add more salt and pepper to your taste.
Feeds 4 to 6.

title: cream puffs
directions: Set oven to 425°.
Place water and butter into pan.
Heat to a rolling boil.
Add the flour all at once and stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves pan and forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat in thoroughly until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Drop from tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet, 3 to 4-inches apart.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and dry.
Let cool slowly on rack, away from drafts.

title: english peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain English peas and reserve liquid.
Mix soup with 1/8 to 1/4 cup of liquid from English peas.
Add English peas and drained asparagus.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with slices of Kraft American cheese.
Let cheese melt.

title: spice cupcakes
directions: Cream eggs, oleo and sweetener together.
Add skim milk.
Then add remaining ingredients, except raisins.
Then fold in raisins. Bake 15 minutes at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes as a cake.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Stir.
Cook 2 minutes on medium heat.
Remove pan from heat and add all other ingredients in order given.
Work quickly.
Stir mixture.
Drop on wax paper in spoonfuls.
You can make cookies as large or as small as you wish.
Work fast so mixture does not get dry.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until blended.
Batter will be very sticky.
Drop by teaspoon into confectioners sugar. Roll lightly to coat.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the first 7 ingredients with mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle the top with shredded cheese and crispy fried bacon, broken into pieces.
Let set at least 24 hours in the refrigerator before serving.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Beat pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, salt and eggs together until well mixed and pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Thinly slice margarine over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Enjoy!!!

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Beat egg whites with mixer until stiff; add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time; until stiff.
Add cream of tartar and salt; stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Cover cookie sheet with wax paper. Drop mixture by a spoon; place in oven.
Turn off oven and leave cookies until oven has cooled.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box; bake.	Immediately after
removing from oven, poke cake full of holes with an ice pick.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt and water for about 5 minutes until bubbly.
Stir constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks to a little hot mixture, then add to the rest of the hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
To this mixture, add butter, lemon rind and lemon juice. Pour in baked pie shell.

title: unique cheese ball
directions: Save some nuts to roll the cheese ball in.
Mix all ingredients; shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in the remaining nuts and chill.

title: mother's molasses gingerbread
directions: Put soda in flour.
Add vinegar to buttermilk, then mix with ingredients as listed.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract; mix well.
Place unwrapped chocolate in microwave dish. Melt; stir melted chocolate into coconut mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheets, 1 inch apart.
Bake 20 minutes until edges are golden brown.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Place in a baking dish. Add cream of mushroom soup and milk together and pour over macaroni; mix gently. Add peas and 1/2 cup cheese (mixed with other).
On top, sprinkle cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
(Cut butter into small pieces.)
Preheat oven to 375° and cook for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken (or turkey) curry in a hurry
directions: *If you make more than you can eat, this leftover becomes a pretty good leftover.

title: chili
directions: In skillet, brown ground chuck.
Put onions in and cook with meat.
Put all seasonings to taste.
After meat and onions is cooked well done, put in crock pot and add all remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock pot on low for 3 hours.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Brown salt pork (or bacon).
Add onion.
Cook until yellow. Add potatoes, carrot, green pepper, tomatoes, salt, pepper, bay leaf, celery, thyme and water.
Boil gently until potatoes and green pepper are done.
Shuck the clams, reserving the liquid and coarsely chop the clams.
Strain the liquid.
Add clams and clam liquid to the soup.
Add bottled clam juice for more flavor/additional liquid.
May add canned baby clams, if desired.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread into crust. Layer in strawberries, pineapple and sliced bananas.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: harvard beets
directions: Blend cornstarch and sugar. Stir in liquid, vinegar and salt. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Add beets and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut the chicken into small pieces.
In large skillet or wok heat oil; stir-fry the chicken 1 minute.
In small bowl combine ginger, soy sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in frozen vegetables and onion; cover.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring once.
In small bowl combine flour and water until smooth; gradually add to chicken mixture.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Trim off fat; bake ribs 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
Pour off fat and pour sauce over ribs.
Cook 1/2 hour more.

title: mulled cider
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer on low until hot. Can be stored and reheated.

title: cherry cha cha
directions: Mix crust ingredients and spread in 8 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream and add marshmallows.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over cold crust.
Then spoon over cherry pie filling.
Place remaining cream mixture over filling.
Top with 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.
Top with a cherry.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix butter, shortening and peanut butter.
Add other ingredients and mix like pie crust.
Press on a cookie sheet and bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Frost with Chocolate Powdered Sugar Frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Stir all ingredients well.

title: sugar plums
directions: With knife, process in food processor the prunes, dates and apricots.
Chop for 1 minute or until finely chopped.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add pecans, graham cracker crumbs and rinds.
Mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 or 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: patsy's broccoli soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients except cheese.
Add cheese and continue simmering until cheese melts.
Very easy and delicious!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Cut up artichokes, keep oil for tossing. Slice black olives.
Thaw vegetables under running water and drain. Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Use oil from artichokes and Italian dressing to toss everything with. Use as much as you like. Salt and pepper to taste and refrigerate.
You can substitute tortellini for pasta and omit bag of vegetables for another pasta salad.

title: modeling dough
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until stiff.
Cool.
It's ready to use.
Store airtight and play with it again and again.
Needs no refrigeration.

title: sausage corn muffins
directions: Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch or line with paper baking cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in baking mix, corn meal, milk, salt and mustard just until moistened.
Fold in corn and sausage.
Divide evenly into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 20 to 22 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12.

title: zegediner gulasch
directions: Roast onion in Crisco until light brown.
Sprinkle paprika over onion.
Add water and cubed meat; cover and let cook about 1/2 hour.
Then add sauerkraut, apples, bouillon cubes, bay leaves and enough water to cover sauerkraut; salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 2 hours.
Mix sour cream with flour and a little water to smooth; add to sauerkraut mix.
Let simmer a couple more minutes.

title: picnic rice
directions: Fold 32-inch length of heavy-duty foil in half; press into a large bowl to form pouch.
Add all ingredients, except rice. Blend well.
Stir in rice and mix just to moisten.
Seal pouch tightly and remove from bowl.
Place foil pouch on medium hot coals and cook for about 10 minutes.
Rotate pouch and continue cooking about 10 minutes longer.
Open package and fluff rice. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: sweet chex mix
directions: Mix cereal and pecans into very large pan.
Melt brown sugar, butter and Karo syrup;
bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly, then add the vanilla.
Pour over the cereal and mix.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, mixing half way.
Put on wax paper and spread out.

title: dee's nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Sprinkle taco seasoning mix into ground beef with 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
While beef is simmering, cook nacho cheese sauce mix with milk according to package directions.
When this thickens, pour in Ro-Tel tomatoes; do not drain.
Mixture will be thin.
Add Velveeta cheese until desired consistency.
Add ground beef mixture.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chocolate milk mix(low-fat)
directions: Mix in a large storage container.
When ready to make a cup of hot chocolate, use 3 tablespoons per mug to 1 mug of boiling water.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together the salt, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Place on cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop for large cookies or a spoon for regular size cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: jiffy hollandaise
directions: Combine.
Don't boil; heat over low heat until hot.
Serve over asparagus, broccoli, Brussels sprouts or cauliflower.

title: gazpacho shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, combine salsa, yellow pepper, cucumber, lime juice and green onion.
Bring to a boil, simmer over medium heat.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes or just until shrimp turns pink.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve over hot cooked rice or pasta with garlic tortilla chips.
Garnish with avocado, if desired.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Add rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in scallion and almonds.

title: catfish stew
directions: Using large pot, fry the bacon.
Cut heat to low and add a layer of potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add a layer of fish, salt and pepper, then a layer of onion.
Continue in layers until all ingredients are in the pot.
Add water and cover.
Leave on low heat until fish and potatoes are cooked for approximately 30 minutes after water starts steaming.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab cheese appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese, lemon juice, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise and garlic.
Spread on 16-inch diameter plate (small pizza pan or use 10-inch pie plate for thicker).
Cover with chili sauce and flaked crab.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
(Can also use can of shrimp or tuna for topping.)

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Stir in water and cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from stove and add beaten yolks, juice and rind (add to taste), and butter.
Cook for a few minutes longer until thickens again.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Spread Doritos in pan.
Place chicken on top of Doritos. Combine soups, Ro-Tel, chicken broth, onions and chili powder. Pour over chicken; top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: taco quiche
directions: Bake pastry shell at 400° for 7 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet. Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Stir in ground beef, chili powder, oregano, salt, cayenne, catsup and red pepper sauce. Brown meat; break up into crumbly mixture.
Drain off any liquid. Spoon into baked pie shell.
Beat eggs.
Mix in half and half, salt, chilies and cheese.
Pour mixture over meat.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes until center is set and a knife comes out clean.
Let rest 15 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of unsalted, boiling water about 10 minutes, until crisp-tender.
In a bowl, mix eggs, cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Arrange broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon cheese mixture atop.
Stir together the bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture; bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through and egg mixture is set.
Serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken divan(microwave)
directions: Wash, trim and remove lower stalks of broccoli.
Divide into equal size spears.
Arrange broccoli in microwave dish with water; cover and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, turning dish every 4 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli so flowerets face outside of dish.
Cut chicken into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Place in shallow baking dish without overlapping. Combine wine and basil; pour over chicken.
Cover and microwave on Medium 7 to 9 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Combine butter and mushrooms in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Remove chicken from wine mixture, reserving 1/4 cup.
Layer chicken over broccoli in center of dish. Top with mushrooms.
Combine sour cream, curry powder and reserved wine mixture; spread over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, 8 minutes on High, turning after 4 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour and spices.
Peel and dice apples.
Add apples and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Mine takes 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.)

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine cubed chicken, chopped celery, halved grapes and pecans in large mixing bowl. Add mayonnaise and sour cream; mix thoroughly. Chill well before serving. Serve with snack crackers such as Chicken in a Biskit.

title: crab dip
directions: Chop crab meat fine.
Mix with cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Add to crab mixture.
Add 1/2 of cocktail sauce.
Stir well.
Put rest of cocktail sauce on top. Serve chilled with crackers.

title: mexican eggs
directions: Saute pepper, onion and tomato.
Pour in eggs and cook at low heat.
Heat tortillas.
Put eggs in hot tortillas; roll up and eat.

title: apple bran muffins(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients except applesauce.
Stir in applesauce. Spray twelve 2 1/2-inch diameter muffin pans with a nonstick spray.
Pour an equal amount of batter into each baking cup.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until done.
Muffins are best when completely cooled.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Empty oysters and broth in a pan.
Roll out oyster crackers fine and mix with oysters (add a little dry bread).
Season with salt.
Mix together and stuff 1 turkey or 2 chickens.
If too dry, add a little water.

title: chicken kiev country style
directions: Dip pieces of chicken in melted butter, then in cheese and bread crumb mixture (with parsley and garlic mixed in).
Place in baking dish and cover with Saran wrap.
Cook in microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Remove wrap and add leftover melted butter (1/4 cup), wine and scallions.
Cover and heat for 5 minutes on High. (I serve it over rice.)
Serves 3 to 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease small casserole.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain and mix in egg, mayo, soup and cheese. Crush 5 or 6 crackers and spread on bottom of casserole.
Pour in broccoli mixture, then top with more crushed crackers.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
May be prepared in advance.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake(8 servings)
directions: Coat micro pan by using solid shortening or butter.
In medium bowl, combine cake mix, oil, water, 1/4 cup peanut butter and egg. Beat with spoon 75 strokes or until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake on High 6 1/2 to 8 minutes, until cake pulls away from pan.
Immediately invert onto serving plate.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and add to your favorite stir-fried vegetables when vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir and cook until thickened.

title: candied apples (dip)
directions: Mix well and chill.
Especially good with Granny Smith apples!

title: virginia williams salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Slowly add oil and beat with electric mixer.
Add other ingredients.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers, remove tops and seeds.
Place upright in a 2-quart microproof casserole.
Pour water over bottom of dish and cook, covered, on High 2 minutes.
Drain water and let peppers stand while preparing filling.

title: twinkies dessert
directions: Take Twinkies sliced lengthwise.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan, then mix pudding and spread over Twinkies; let cool, then add large Cool Whip and cover with nuts.

title: yellow pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed (450 strokes by hand).
Scrape bowl often.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until it springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool right side up for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Use your favorite topping.

title: butterscotch-brown rice pudding
directions: Place milk in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
(Do not boil.)
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot milk into eggs; add to remaining hot milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in rice, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels.
Place dish in a shallow pan; add water to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Remove dish from pan.
Let pudding cool slightly before serving.
This is low-fat.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Open can of biscuits and separate.
Let them set for a few minutes.
Stretch and pull on biscuit to make a long strip; wrap around the wiener from one end to the other.
Place on cookie sheet and bake according to the oven temperature on the can of biscuits. Bake until lightly brown.

title: mom's fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. Mix together oil, sugar, and eggs. Beat vigorously for 2 minutes. Stir together 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into oil mixture alternately with pineapple juice. Mix well. In a large bowl place candied fruits and the nuts. Mix in 1 cup sifted flour. Be sure to cover fruit and nuts thoroughly. Pour batter over floured fruit and mix thoroughly. Line an angel food pan, or 2 loaf pans with oiled brown paper, and pour batter into pan. Place a pan of water on lower oven rack. Bake cake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until done. Let cake cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool. Remove paper. Place a small shot glass with rum in it in the center cake. Soak a piece of cheesecloth in rum and wrap around cake. Wrap in foil or put in a covered cake pan. Age at least 4 weeks. Longer it sets the better it is.

title: many chip cookies
directions: Using a mixer, whip the first 6 ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix the flour, baking soda and salt. Add the flour mixture to the first bowl. Mix by hand until moist. Next, add 1 1/2 packages each of vanilla, chocolate and butterscotch onto a cookie tray. Bake at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, eggs, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into balls.
Brown.
In separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Simmer 4 hours.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Cut up small 1 head lettuce, 5 shredded carrots, 1 large package Cheddar cheese, 1 package bacon (fried and crumbled), 1 large onion and 1 can peas (drained).
Radishes and celery are optional.
Mix vegetables together.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill about 5 minutes.
Fold Cool Whip or whipped cream; mix well.
Line a 2 1/2-quart bowl with vanilla wafers; cover with layer of bananas, then layer of pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding mix on top. Refrigerate.

title: junk
directions: Blend all together and refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and mix with sugar, waffle syrup, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes or until lightly browned, at 375°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream well the shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add water and soda.
Cream well with electric mixer.
Then add and mix by spoon the flour, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop on a cookie sheet with a teaspoon and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread with marshmallow cream.
Cool completely and spread with icing.

title: cheesy crust pizza
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine 1 cup flour, yeast, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add very warm water to flour mixture.
Mix until almost smooth.
Knead on floured surface 2 to 3 minutes.
Cover dough and let rest for 5 to 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 2 parts with well floured or greased fingers; press each half into greased 12-inch pizza pan, forming a rim around edge.
Spread half of sauce over dough.
Put on toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edge is crisp and brown and cheeses are melted.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Beat brown sugar, butter, flour and egg yolks.
Add liquid; cook in double boiler until proper consistency.

title: carrot salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Prepare jello as directed on box.
Use reserved juice instead of cold water.
Chill until set.
Fold in pineapple and carrots.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Mix flour with small amount of milk to make a thick paste.
Mix together broth, milk and soup.
Heat and stir in paste.
Cook on medium heat, stirring often, until thick.
Add pimento, chicken and eggs.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over crisp chow mein noodles.

title: grilled banana dessert
directions: Peel a 1-inch strip from banana.
Do not remove.
Cutting down to the peel, remove the exposed banana.
Place chocolate chips and marshmallows into the hollowed out banana.
Replace the banana strip.
Replace the peel and wrap in tinfoil.
Set on grill or hot coals for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Place chicken breasts and other ingredient in casserole.
Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken ball
directions: Beat with mixer. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Shape into ball. Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat with a rotary mixer or whisk beater until smooth. Pour in pan of oil in a circular motion and turn when brown.
Oil should be 350°.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar or cinnamon sugar.

title: coconut cream layer pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, topping mix, milk and 2 teaspoons vanilla until light and fluffy. Pour into pie shells. Spread 1 cup coconut on each pie and chill several hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook lasagne, but not until soft, in 6 quarts of water for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Separate lasagne out flat on wax paper or aluminum foil to cool.
Combine cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper for filling.
Pour about 1/2 cup meat sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange 4 pieces of lasagne lengthwise over sauce, overlapping the edges.
Spread 1/3 of the cheese filling over lasagne.
Cover with about 1 cup meat sauce.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour.
Add egg yolks and juice of lemon and rind (1/4 cup of lemon juice may be used instead of lemon).
Add milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites last and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350°.

title: sausage soup
directions: Put all ingredients together; cover with water and cook slowly until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Cook rice as directed. Mix all together. Can be served warm or cold. Can also be made a day ahead.

title: deviled eggs
directions: * Such as prepared mustard, chopped capers (optional), salt, onion powder, garlic powder, cayenne, freshly ground pepper, dill weed, horseradish sauce.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Drizzle this mixture well with olive oil.
Season with seasoned salt and ground cumin.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours and serve with chips.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients (except oysters).
Add chicken broth until like cornbread batter.
Stir in oysters.
Pour in a buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 400° or until golden brown.

title: nellie's old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water for 20 to 30 minutes; cool.
Drain water off and add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: kay's cheese cake
directions: Grease free-form pan.
Make a zwieback or vanilla wafer crust. Line pan with crust.
Bake 5 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.
Mix Ricotta and cream cheese together until smooth.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and melted butter.
Add to cheese and eggs and beat with whisk until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Put in 325° oven and bake for 1 hour. Leave in oven and turn oven off.
Leave it for 8 hours.
Remove and cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot chocolate(from scratch)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy a hot cup of chocolate the cheap way.
Store in an airtight container in cabinet.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rapid chicken
directions: Saute onion and chicken in a small amount of oil until chicken turns white.
Drain.
Combine the tomato sauce, picante sauce, cumin, oregano and basil and add to chicken.
Place the zucchini on top.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve immediately.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and mix well.
Add flavoring; add flour mixed with spices.
Add nuts and fruit; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
Approximately 75 cookies.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Break egg into blender.
Add all ingredients, except 3/4 cup oil.
Cover.
Turn motor on low.
Uncover and pour in remaining 3/4 cup oil in a steady stream.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Boil celery, carrots and potatoes which are cut into small pieces until tender.
Add peas and spaghetti (broken into small pieces), seasoning and V-8 juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup.
Cook until soft ball forms.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful on buttered cookie sheet.

title: easy oyster dip
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Saut onion in margarine.
Mix all other ingredients and cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers or other appetizers.
This dish also freezes well.

title: cherry waldorf salad
directions: Bring 3/4 cup of apple juice to a boil in small saucepan. Stir boiling juice into gelatin in a large bowl.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Mix rest of apple juice and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a serving dish.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Makes 5 servings.
Can be doubled.
Contains 110 calories per serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
(Do not allow ingredients to stand too long before baking.)
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until noodles are tender.

title: "mom o'brien bread pudding"
directions: Break bread up until large Pyrex bowl is almost full.
In another bowl, mix sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add the eggs; stir again.
Add quite a bit of milk; stir and pour over bread.
If not enough liquid to cover bread thoroughly, add more.
Place in a 350° oven until brown.

title: twistin' pasta salad(makes 6 to 8 servings.)
directions: In large bowl, blend Italian dressing, mustard and pepper. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mother's homemade white bread
directions: Mix in large glass 1/2 cup warm water, a dash of sugar, and the yeast.
In a large bowl mix honey, salt, butter and 2 cups hot water (hot enough to melt honey and butter).
Gradually add several cups of flour and stir together.
When dough is cool enough add the yeast mixture.
Add more flour until dough is too thick to stir.
Put the dough on a lightly floured board and knead enough of the remaining flour in until the dough is still elastic but not sticky.
Lightly grease mixing bowl and add dough; lightly grease top of dough.
Cover bowl with a clean dish towel and place in a warm, draft free location.
Let rise until doubled in size, about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Punch dough down and knead again on lightly floured surface.
When all of the air pockets have been kneaded out, divide dough into 2 portions, shape each portion into a loaf, and place in a lightly greased loaf pan.
Lightly butter the top of each loaf, cover with a towel, and allow to rise again for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole(makes 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook unpeeled whole potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Slip off skins and mash potatoes until smooth. Add eggs, cream, butter, orange and lemon rind, salt, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart saucepan over low heat, heat butter until melted; remove saucepan from heat.
With wire whisk, beat in corn syrup, sugar, eggs and vanilla until blended. Arrange pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Carefully pour egg mixture over them.
Bake for 1 hour, or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool pie on wire rack.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil together.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together; add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: lunch box cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Cream butter, shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour and cinnamon.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in oats and Raisin Bran.
Drop by tablespoons about 2-inches apart.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes or until bottoms are lightly brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan or other dish. Bake for 1 hour.
Let set 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour 1 cup of water over the top.
Place in covered dish and bake 30 - 45 minutes until done.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar, melted butter, pineapple and cubes of bread.
Mix well; place mixture in baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and/or allspice.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart bowl, mix together the milk, onion, salt, pepper, flour and butter.
Cook in the microwave until milk comes to a boil.
Add potatoes and stir.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: baked tomato macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add cheese and tomatoes. Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Combine with macaroni and mix well.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: flap jacks(camp style)
directions: Place flour in mixing bowl.
Add milk and water.
Mix well, adding water as needed to make batter medium thick.
Use 10-inch cast iron skillet.
Melt shortening on camp stove enough to cover bottom of pan.
Pour batter into pan to cover bottom with thin layer in 3/4 circle for one large flap-jack.
Fry until bubbly and brown on under side.
Flip into air and turn (hopefully) catching back in pan.
Add shortening as needed while cooking and after each one is cooked, brown other side and remove from pan.
Finish cooking other flap jacks.
Eat with eggs, bacon, jelly, jam, syrup, etc.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Combine butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts. Sift in flour and mix well.
Drop the dough by teaspoons onto a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15minutes. Roll cookies in confectioners sugar while still hot.
Roll again after cool.

title: pizzaburger
directions: Lightly mix ground beef, onion, salt, oregano, pepper and 1/2 cup pizza sauce.
Shape into 6 patties, 4 1/2 to 5-inches in diameter.
Broil one side, turn and broil other side to desired doneness.
Spoon remaining pizza sauce over patties.
Top with slices of cheese.
Return to broiler just until cheese begins to melt.
Meanwhile, toast muffins.
Serves 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces and dip in butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
If any mixture is left, sprinkle over top before cooking.
Drop in Bundt or tube pan, cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together vegetables, onions, cheese, mayonnaise and chestnuts. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix margarine and Ritz crackers together; put on top. Bake at 350° until bubbling.
Makes 1 quart casserole dish.

title: huhn im burgunder(chicken cooked in burgundy wine)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Cook bacon and onion in it until soft and transparent.
Remove bacon and onion with slotted spoon and reserve.
Brown chicken on all sides in remaining fat.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add brandy, Burgundy, bay leaf, parsley, thyme, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook, covered, in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in reserved bacon and onion and the mushrooms. Return to oven and cook, covered, for another 5 to 10 minutes. Remove; stir remaining butter into the sauce.
Serve with noodles or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.
Cooks great in electric frypan.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put 2 cups seasoned croutons in casserole.
Add milk and shredded cheese (layered). Beat eggs.
Mix with onion, jalapeno pepper, black pepper, seasoning salt and garlic powder.
Pour over croutons and cheese. Crumble crisp bacon over top of egg mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° until well done.
Eat this while it is still warm.

title: tea punch
directions: Boil the water.
Add tea bags and steep for 6 minutes.
Take tea bags out.
Add frozen lemonade with the water it calls for and pineapple juice.
Can add a little mint to taste.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown beef in large soup pot.
Add chopped onion to your satisfaction.
Stir continually.
Add 1 can of cream soup and mix, don't boil!
Add chopped bell pepper (1/4 cup).
Add pinch of salt, pepper, sage, thyme and oregano.
Add cheeses to your satisfaction.
Don't let sit; always stir.
If too thick, add small amount of water to thin.

title: microwave sliced baking potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Pat dry.
Lay wooden spoon beside potato so you won't cut through it.
Cut potato in thin slices (but not all the way through!).
Place potatoes in microwave dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and the herbs.
Microwave on High power for 10 minutes.
(Rearrange potatoes after 5 minutes.)
Let potatoes rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses. Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serves as a side dish or as a main dish with a salad on the side.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown chops.
Drain.
In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes, onion and chops.
Add soup mix blended with water. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes and chops are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add water and vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Chill, tightly covered, for 4 hours.
Shape into ladyfingers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool slightly on wire rack.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: beef poppie
directions: Boil beef and beef broth until beef is done.
Remove 1 cup of broth and beef.
Mix flour, salt and eggs.
Gradually stir in broth to mixture.
Pour in enough broth to make consistency of pie dough.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch squares.
Drop squares into the boiling beef broth.
Stir after all are in.
Reduce heat to a slow simmer.
Let cook for 30 minutes.
Add beef anytime to pot.
Poppie is done when tender.

title: curried orange rice
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan or flameproof casserole; saute onion until soft and golden, but not brown.
Stir in curry and rice; cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir with fork.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid has been absorbed.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix
sugar, brown sugar, butter and eggs together.
Add flour, nuts,
chips and coconut.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan on 300° to 325° for about 1 hour.
Cake will be heavy.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 350° or microwave on High (100%) for 2 minutes.
Turn dish a half turn after 1 minute.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: deb's perfect corn bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Mix with fork until smooth. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan (cast-iron is best).
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: caramel-peanut pie
directions: Place 1 cup sugar in a heavy skillet; cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and forms a light brown syrup.
Reduce heat to low; gradually add boiling water in a slow stream, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Remove from heat.
Combine 1 cup sugar and flour in a heavy saucepan; stir well.
Add egg yolks, milk and caramelized sugar mixture; stir well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in the chopped peanuts and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shells.

title: potato and tomato hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. In roaster layer meat and potatoes. Cover with tomatoes. Put into oven and bake at 350° for half an hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Pickles will appear thick but will develop water when in refrigerator.
Pickles last indefinitely and will stay crisp.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can also add slivered almonds or pecans. Bake in microwave for 6 to 7 minutes or bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Stir until crumbly. Cut bread in 1/2 lengthwise, then in 8 pieces crosswise.
(Each loaf should have 16 pieces.)
Sprinkle 1/4 of topping into each of 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Arrange the pieces in each. Sprinkle each with 1/2 the remaining topping; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (about 1 hour).
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn out of pans immediately.
Serve warm with a glass of milk.
Yum, Yum!

title: brunch casserole
directions: Layer in greased casserole dish the sausage, then the eggs, salt and milk (mixed together), bread and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Leave in oven until cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Make a well in the center of this mixture.
Pour beaten eggs and oil in the well.
Stir until dry ingredients just become moist.
Pour thawed strawberries and juice into a container.
With slotted spoon, dip out berries and gently stir into mixture.
Then add juice gradually, stirring until batter is of proper consistency.
You may not need all of juice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash scallops well and drain on paper towels.
Saute mushrooms and scallions in butter.
Put scallops in well-buttered casserole dish.
Spread sauteed mushrooms and scallions over scallops and top with parsley.
Pour on the chicken broth and squeeze lemon over top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over all.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Bake pastry shells according to package directions.
In medium pan, cook peppers in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk, chicken and pimento; heat, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into warm pastry shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Melt Crisco, then add milk; set aside.
Add all other ingredients together, except flour.
Pour in milk and Crisco, then add flour.
Knead well.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll 1/4-inch thick, spread with oleo and cut pie shaped.
Roll each piece up, starting at large end.
Place on cookie sheet.
May be frozen.
Take out what you want to cook. Let rolls rise before baking.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Mix eggs, sugar and margarine until smooth.
Put 3/4 of crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth batter over crumbs.
Cover with sliced strawberries.
Cover with whipping cream (cream is to be beaten until stiff before topping on strawberries). Sprinkle other 1/4 of crumbs on top; refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage until just tender enough to core and separate leaves.
Thoroughly mix ground beef, salt, pepper, garlic powder, eggs, onion, rice and 4 tablespoons of soup.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 cup meat mixture in a cabbage leaf, folding leaf around meat to form a roll.
Cover the bottom of a Dutch oven or other large heavy pot with cabbage leaves and 1/2 can of sauerkraut.
Place rolls on top of sauerkraut.
Cover rolls with remaining 1/2 can of sauerkraut and any excess cabbage leaves.
Mix 2 cans of tomato soup with 4 cans water, 2 tablespoons vinegar and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimiento and mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners to top center; twist and seal.
Brush top with 1 tablespoon butter.
Dip in crouton crumbs. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4.

title: cherry nut cake - ma's
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and egg yolks well beaten.
Sift the flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with liquids.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; add to mixture.
Bake in two oiled layer cake pans for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: easy frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together well.
Add rest of ingredients (except Cool Whip and nuts); mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts last.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Freeze. Keeps well 2 to 3 weeks in freezer.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread 1 cup sauce.
Arrange a layer of noodles.
Top with a portion of all other ingredients. Repeat layers until all are used.
Gently press pieces into cheese mixture.
Make sure sauce covers top and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Fry the bacon; crumble and set aside.
Drain most of grease out of skillet.
Saute the pepper and onion.
Add the eggplant and remaining ingredients, except cheese and bread crumbs.
Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add crumbled bacon and about a cup of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into lightly greased casserole; top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and spices, bring to boil.
Add ground pears, peppers and onions and cook until all ingredients are good and hot (5 to 10 minutes).
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to the package.
Set aside to drain.
In a separate container, combine 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese plus the next 7 ingredients.
This is the cheese mixture. Stuff each shell with this mixture.
Pour half of the spaghetti sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange the shells in the sauce.
Pour the remaining sauce over the shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add the remaining cup of Mozzarella cheese over the top and bake for 5 more minutes or until cheese is browned.
Makes 7 to 9 shells.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream the margarine.
Mix in sugar substitute, water and vanilla.
Add egg substitute to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick spray and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and melted oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread out on bottom.
Mix jello and water, cool.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Beat well chilled canned milk well. Mix together and put in pan on top of graham crust.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: eggplant caponata
directions: Brown eggplant in a little olive oil.
Saute onions in olive oil until soft and golden.
Saute celery in olive oil until soft and golden.
In small saucepan, mix sugar and wine vinegar.
Add eggplant and all other remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Refrigerate.
Keeps in refrigerator 5 days.
Can be frozen.
Serve with pita or bagel chips.

title: peach cobbler #2(microwave)
directions: In a glass dish, crumble 4 cookies and spread on bottom. Empty pie filling on top of cookies.
Top with 4 remaining crumbled cookies.
Heat in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: marilyn vegetables
directions: Mix celery, pepper, green beans, peas and pimentos together. Mix remainder of ingredients and add to vegetables.
Marinate overnight, then drain.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut butter into flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar with pastry cutter until it looks like coarse meal.
Press firmly into baking pan; arrange peaches on surface to cover.
Sprinkle fruit with mixture of cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Pour beaten egg yolks with cream over top and bake 40 minutes longer at 375°.
Serves up to 12.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown sugar and eggs and a little milk at a time.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage roll
directions: Let bread dough rise as directed, then press out on a greased cookie sheet.
Brown sausage.
Add chopped onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Stir in raw egg.
Add 6 to 8 crushed crackers to absorb moisture.
Spread on bread.
Roll up and seal, placing sealed side down.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Slice and serve hot.

title: moist and minty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring just to a boil; remove from heat. Add 1 cup Nestle Toll House mint flavored semi-sweet chocolate morsels and vanilla extract, stirring until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour mixture and remaining Nestle Toll House mint morsels.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes, just until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares. Makes 16 brownies.

title: vanilla bavarian cream
directions: Blend thoroughly first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil.
Place pan in cold water; cool until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla. Pour into buttered 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm (about 4 hours).
Unmold on large serving dish.
Garnish with fruit.

title: hardy hero
directions: Slice bread in half; butter both pieces.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese; spread mixture on buttered bread. Place bread on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°; ten minutes before end of baking, place cheese on top of mixture.

title: jennifer's pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on large plate with edges slightly up. Spread chile sauce, mixed with mustard, on top of cream cheese. Sprinkle basil, tomato, pepper, pepperoni and cheese on top.
Add crackers around edge of pizza before serving.

title: david's jambalaya
directions: Clean squirrel. Wash good and brown meat.
Add onion, bell pepper and parsley.
Let simmer. Add water, salt, rice, pepper and Kitchen Bouquet. Stir.
Bring to a boil, then lower fire and cover.
Let cook until rice is puffy.
Now enjoy some good cooking.

title: acadian alligator sauce piquant
directions: Never use internal organs, such as livers, hearts, gizzards or kidneys in making stock.
They contain blood which gives stock a very strong and unpleasant taste.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large container that can be sealed for storage.
Use 1/4 cup mixture for each cup of hot chocolate mix with hot water.

title: corn delight
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: family favorite
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Brown meat; drain. Add onion and green peppers; cook until tender.
Combine ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a casserole dish; add rice, onion soup, water and soy sauce.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Spoon on soups.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes to brown.

title: date cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to other mixture with cut up dates.
Place complete mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Drizzle powdered sugar frosting when taking them from the oven.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt with the Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Then thaw 30 minutes before serving.

title: three-lettuce salad
directions: In a screw-top jar, combine olive oil, vinegar, garlic and salt.
Cover.
Shake until well blended.
Chill until serving time.

title: plum conserve
directions: Wash plums and cover with water in large kettle.
Cook until tender, cool.
Remove pits and chop.
To plums add sugar, grated lemon peel, slices of oranges and lemon.
Cook together until thick and clear.
Add walnuts.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 6 jelly glasses.
Excellent with beef.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients with electric beater until light and fluffy.
Roll into little balls with floured hands.
Place into a pan with tablespoon melted margarine and cook until done.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Place cereal in a large mixing bowl.
Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter until melted; mix well and pour over cereal.
Coat cereal with mixture.
Put powdered sugar in a large plastic bag.
Put coated cereal in same bag.
Shake until cereal is coated with powdered sugar.
Your snack is now ready to eat!

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pour off water from grated potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
With spoon, drop mixture into hot oil. Fry on both sides until crisp and golden brown.
Drain on brown paper or paper towels.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork (dipped in flour to prevent sticking).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding into the Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at low speed.
Slowly add juice mixture until well blended.
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell. Bake 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, top with whipped cream or meringue and lime slices, if preferred.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together all other ingredients and coat chicken.
Place, skin sides down, in pan. Bake 35 minutes (425°); turn.
Bake until done, 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake and icing
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix sugars, oil and eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash.
Slice.
Cook gently with salt and water.
Drain water.
Mash butter into squash.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir. Bake at 350° in buttered casserole dish for 20 to 30 minutes until set.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Add chilies, corn and cheese.
Add corn meal; mix well.
Pour in a greased pan and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: p-nut butter cream cheese pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in peanut butter.

In separate bowl, beat pudding and milk. Let set about 10 minutes. Combine pudding mix to creamed mixture; stir well. Add Cool Whip. Blend. Pour in a pie shell. Chill well before serving. Garnish with chocolate shavings or Cool Whip.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Squeeze.
Combine spinach with all ingredients; mix well.
Shape spinach mixture into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 11 dozen.

title: mom's butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour together; add the beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook in double boiler or copper bottom pan until mixture is real thick; stir constantly.
Do not let it scorch. Add vanilla and butter.
Let cool, then put in baked pie shells. Cover with meringue.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown bacon; crumble after frying and drain.
Brown hamburg and onion.
Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook the cut up onion and margarine in a small pot.
Drain can of salmon.
Dump salmon in a bowl and take the bones out if you desire.
Mash the salmon up a little and cook a while in the pot of onion and margarine.
Put milk in a bigger pot and start to warm.
After salmon and ingredients have cooked a little while, dump into milk and serve when it gets hot enough.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into small balls and freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in Ziploc bags in freezer overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth, add all other ingredients mix well, roll into ball and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip torte
directions: Add together dates, boiling water and soda.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs alternately.
Add flour and date mixture, blending well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips on top of cake.
