Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: vanilla almond coffee
directions: Add vanilla and almond extract to coffee.
Shake to blend thoroughly.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until stiff. Add vanilla, pecans and chips.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoonful onto foil lined cookie sheets.
Place in preheated oven (350°).
Turn oven off.
Do not open door for 8 hours.

title: baked fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a baggie.
Shake chicken to coat.
Put coated chicken on a cookie sheet with melted butter. Cook 30 minutes at 425°.
Turn over; cook 15 minutes more.

title: moist pie crust mix
directions: Mix thoroughly salt, vegetable shortening and flour until forms tiny beads throughout.
Add water.
Mix well.
Divide into portions (appropriate amounts for 1 pie crust).
Wrap each portion in plastic wrap first, then in foil.
Freeze until ready to use.
Can be kept 3 to 4 months in freezer if wrapped well.

title: southerner pressed chicken
directions: Boil til she's done, then bone it.
Remove fat and skin.
In a large bowl, mix the old girl, after chopping her up, with celery and pimento.
Set aside.
Meantime, melt 3 1/2 packages plain gelatin in 1 cup of chicken stock.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, salad dressin', salt and pepper.
Mix real good and press into a glass dish.
Chill and yawl have got a scrumpous dish.

title: ethel's pumpkin bread
directions: Add the hot water to the raisins; let cool.
Cream together the shortening, sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, soda, cloves, allspice, baking powder and salt.
Add nut meats.
Mix together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese; add uncooked sausage.
Add Bisquick.
Mix well. Make into balls and bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meat skillet dinner
directions: Cook beef, green pepper and onion in a large frypan until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in rice.
Cover and cook over low heat about 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Add little water during cooking if needed.

title: russian tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 4 minutes (no longer). Add to cold water.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and cloves.
Simmer (do not boil) until hot.
Serves 16.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate wings at joints.
Cut off tips. Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain chicken, saving marinade.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Turn chicken and bake 30 more minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place lettuce in salad bowl.
Add cauliflower.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over cauliflower.
Add bacon and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Toss gently just before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: baked corn with cheese topping
directions: Drain corn.
Place in a shallow 9-inch dish.
Saute green onions in butter; sprinkle with brown sugar.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, mustard, black pepper and Cheddar cheese. Spoon mixture over corn and onions; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Cook all ingredients together, except beans.
Add them later.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Spread peaches in a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine margarine, milk, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar in a bowl.
Mix well. Spoon evenly over peaches.
Mix 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana quick bread
directions: Blend sugar, salt and sugar. Add eggs, flour, soda, bananas and pecans.
Bake in well greased loaf pan at 350 degree oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: diet dessert
directions: Mix all together, then serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil oleo, brown sugar and Karo syrup 5 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over corn.
Put in oven at 250°.
Stir from bottom up every 15 minutes for about 45 minutes.
(Watch it carefully.)

title: baked pheasant
directions: Quarter pheasants or half quail.
Dip in seasoned flour and brown in butter.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms, almonds, onion and celery in butter.
Place game in Dutch oven over sauteed mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add cream, salt, pepper and sherry.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until birds are tender.
(Can cook in glass dish, just watch closer.)

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix dates, pineapple, cherries and nuts with 1/2 cup flour, mix well, add whiskey.
Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 18-20 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies. These freeze well.

title: praline bars
directions: Break the crackers into 3 sections and line bottom of a 10 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bring butter and sugar to a boil and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour evenly over crackers and add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes and lift out with spatula onto wax paper or foil to cool completely.
Yields 40 bars.

title: top hats
directions: Spread one side of crackers with peanut butter.
Place one marshmallow on each of 24 crackers.
Place remaining crackers on top of marshmallows.
Lo-top hats!!

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: family recipe chicken soup
directions: Note:
Can put carrots, celery and onion in processor.

title: party mints
directions: Combine butter, hot water, candy oil and several drops of food coloring in a medium bowl. Gradually add confectioners sugar, mixing thoroughly to make a very stiff, smooth candy. Shake small plastic or rubber molds in granulated sugar. Press a small amount of candy into each mold, leveling off the bottom. Unmold onto waxed paper and "dry" lightly covered at room temperature for at least 24 hours. Store airtight in a cool, dry place.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all but nuts and chips.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 450° or lightly brown.

title: very dainty chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, then add both sugars and cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Dissolve baking soda in 1/8 cup hot water and add to mixture.
Blend in flour well. Stir in nuts. Using a cookie scoop or level soup spoon, drop
dough onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple raisin snack cake(diabetic dessert)
directions: Beat oil and eggs together.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, apple, raisins and apple juice. Mix well and pour into a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
These freeze well.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: banana pecan honey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and line the bottom with parchment or waxed paper.
Sift together 2 1/2 cups flour and baking soda; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine bananas, milk, honey and vanilla; set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Finely chop chipped beef; add some to cheese mixture and other ingredients.
Form into ball; roll ball in remaining chipped beef. Serve with party crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix with fork Crisco, flour, baking powder, salt and egg. Add water and mix with fork until ready to roll.
Roll thin and cut into squares (about 2 inches).
Drop in boiling broth.
(Be sure each piece is wet before adding another to prevent sticking together.)
Cook stewing chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from pot.
Add potatoes and onions to the broth.
When the broth returns to boiling, drop the above pot pie in according to directions.
Cook over low heat until potatoes and onions are soft and pot pie is done (approximately 45 minutes).
Fifteen minutes before it is done, add a pack of peas.
Serve with the chicken or cut chicken into small pieces and add to the pot.

title: pecan cake
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Separate eggs and beat yolks until they are lemony.
Beat whites until they form stiff peaks.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.	Add yolks, mixing well.
Dissolve instant coffee in water and then mix with milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients; mix well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites and pecans.
Bake in oiled and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: harvest fruit tart
directions: Bake shell at 375° for 15 minutes.
In mixer bowl, beat sour cream, sweetened condensed milk, juice concentrate, egg, vanilla and cinnamon; pour into shell.
Bake 30 minutes or until set. Cool.
In skillet, cook apples in margarine until tender.
Arrange on pie; top with glaze.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of the water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
In large bowl, mix 2 cups water, sugar, oil and salt; stir.
Add flour and yeast alternately, mixing well.
Knead for 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Set dough to rise in an oiled bowl; mix down every 10 minutes for 4 times; let rise 10 minutes more, then divide dough into thirds.
Shape each into long loaf and place on greased cookie sheet.
Make 3 slashes diagonally on each loaf.
Cover and let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash almondine
directions: In saucepan, just cover squash and onion with water.
Cook until tender and drain.
Mix with cheese, eggs, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend butter, crumbs and almonds and sprinkle on squash.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
May be prepared ahead.
Serves 8.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Beat sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beat and add syrup; mix well.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in greased pan.

title: cheese with port
directions: Grate cheese very fine, then warm to room temperature.
Beat together with soft butter until fluffy.
Stir in Port gently so as to leave streaks of color.
Press into a ball and roll in nuts, paprika or parsley or pack in serving crock.
Refrigerate a few days before using.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: frozen lemon and pineapple pie
directions: Combine the pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts, lemon peel, lemon juice and reserved pineapple syrup.
Stir to blend.
Spoon into crust.
Cover and freeze for several hours until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, syrup, vanilla and flour.
Mix well and add pecans.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: savory spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Chill 1/2 hour. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper. Roll spinach mixture into small balls. rounded tsp. or tbsp. Bake 15 minutes.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix ingredients (except Sprite) in a gallon container.
Add enough water to make a gallon.
Freeze in 2 Ziploc bags at least 2 days before ready to serve.
Defrost one hour before serving. When ready to serve, add one 2 liter bottle of Sprite or Slice per bag.
Should be icy and slushy.
Is a delicious punch for parties or showers.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Peel and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: reese cups
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter. Place in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Pour melted chocolate over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: refried potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Let cool.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Put on plate and cover with cheese and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: rump roast
directions: Place 2 long sheets (crossways) of heavy-duty aluminum foil in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place roast in center.
Cover roast top and bottom with celery soup, then sprinkle all over with dry soup mix. Wrap very tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Do not touch until completely baked.
Open and you will have roast with its own gravy.

title: sweet 'n sour dinner
directions: Dipping Batter:
Mix beaten egg, milk, flour, salt and baking powder.
Dip meat in mixture and fry until golden brown.

title: easy, cheesy asparagus bake
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving a few pieces for garnish, if desired, and place in shallow 1-quart baking dish with red pepper.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins(yields 1 dozen muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease the muffin tin or line with paper muffin cups.
In a bowl, mix together all the dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, mix together the egg, milk, margarine and brown sugar.
Beat.
Stir in blueberries and nuts. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients all at once and fold in until the dry ingredients are just moistened.
Spoon batter into the muffin cups.
Bake until lightly browned, about 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels in hot water in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Let cool.
In large bowl, cream butter.
Add sugar about 2 tablespoons at a time.
Cream until light and fluffy. Beat in flour, salt and beaten eggs.
Stir in the melted caramels. Add milk, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes which has been preheated.
Turn oven off and let set in oven 15 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Put pear halves onto serving dish.
Put 1/2 to 1 teaspoon mayonnaise in scooped-out area of pear.
Top with grated cheese and cherry.
This can also be made with peach halves.

title: strawberry jam(freezer)
directions: Mash the strawberries; add the sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Heat the water and Sure-Jell; stir into berry mixture.
Stir 2 or 3 minutes.
Put in jars or containers; let stand 24 to 48 hours, then put in freezer.
This is very, very good!!!

title: eggnog cheesecake
directions: Butter 9 in. springform pan.
Combine crumbs, butter, sugar in small bowl and mix well.
Pat crumb mixture over bottom and 3/4 up sides of prepared pan.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a glass baking dish. (We use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.)
Cover with a sprinkling of cashews.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: judy's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour and milk.
Cook until coats spoon.
Let cool.
Add Pet milk, whipping cream and vanilla.
Pour in freezer can and freeze
with plenty of ice and salt.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake at 350° in three 9-inch cake pans.
Cool and frost.

title: appetizer pork dogs
directions: You will need 12 toothpicks.

title: jimmy carter's peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar; slowly add milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put into graham cracker crusts, sprinkle top with peanuts, then freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: libby's overnight chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter; stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap one teaspoon dough around each olive, covering completely.
Arrange on slightly greased baking sheet. Refrigerate.
Bake puffs in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: butterscotch delights
directions: Combine butterscotch pieces and peanut butter in double boiler.
Cook and stir over hot water until mixture is smooth and melted.
Remove from heat and stir in corn flakes and coconut. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Chill until set.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet on high, put 3 tablespoons margarine, cut up chicken breasts, cut up cabbage, cut up zucchini, cut water chestnuts, cut onion and 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Cook on high 10 to 15 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Melt butter and let cool to room temperature.
Beat eggs until foamy, then add flour, sugar, brown sugar and blend in butter. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
May be frozen.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Fry
bacon and chop.
Brown hamburg and onion.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Add water and butter; cook to boiling.
Lower heat; cook for about 8 minutes longer.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix salsa suprema and Italian dressing.
Mix with angel hair noodles (cooked as directed).
Chill overnight.
Before serving, add sliced vegetables such as tomatoes, mushrooms, green onions, radishes, peppers, cucumbers, etc.
Add more dressing, if needed.

title: cheese-filled phyllo triangles
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot. Add onion and saute until tender. Remove from heat and add to mixture the	cheese,

egg and seasoning. Set aside. Cut phyllo sheets lengthwise into 2-inch strips; brush 1 strip with melted butter. Place 1 teaspoon cheese mixture at base of phyllo strip; fold like a flag into triangles. Place seam side down on greased cookie sheets; brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread biscuits to fit shape of 9 x 11-inch pan; cover entire bottom.
Spread cooked and crumbled bacon and sausage evenly on top of biscuit layer, then ham.
Mix eggs in large bowl.

Add cheese to egg mixture or sprinkle on top of bacon and sausage. Pour egg mixture evenly into pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done. Cut into squares, circles or pizza shapes. Enjoy.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash.
Add salt, cinnamon and a dash of nutmeg.
Beat egg yolks.
Fold into squash.
Beat whites until stiff.
Fold into the mixture.
Bake in pan placed in a pan of hot water 1-inch deep in water.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Blend cake mix according to box directions.
Pour half of batter into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in butter and milk.
Pour over the partially cooked cake. Sprinkle with half of the chocolate chips and half of the pecans. Pour the remaining batter over the chips and pecans.
Add chips and pecans for top layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: latkes
directions: Mix ingredients together except oil.
In skillet, fill with 1/4 inch oil and heat.
Drop potato mixture 1 tablespoon at a time into oil and flatten with spatula.
Fry Latkes for 2 minutes.
Turn over and fry until brown.
Serve while warm.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter, salt and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add milk and remainder of sugar, alternating until spreading consistency and add vanilla.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Pour 1 cup water into saucepan.
Add butter.
Bring to boil. Add flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Remove from heat and let cool for 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn dog twists
directions: Will also need 8 wooden sticks.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Combine tomato sauce, beef bouillon, garlic powder, chili powder, onion and green pepper and simmer.
Add hamburger, rice and 3/4 of the cheese.
Put the remaining cheese on top after placing in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: daddy's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions, garlic in bacon grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil, take off fire.
It is ready to eat. This sauce can be frozen.
This is a sweet and spicy sauce.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape meat mixture into 6 loaves.
Place on a rack in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 10 minutes, rearranging loaves after 5 minutes.
Microwave at High an additional 2 minutes, or until done.
Slice cheese in half diagonally.
Place a cheese triangle on each loaf.
Cover loosely with foil; let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl until soft peaks form.
Stir together skim milk, corn syrup and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat in Baking Mix at low speed until blended.
Fold in 1/4 of egg whites until blended.
Gently fold in remaining egg whites just until blended.
Divide batter evenly between 2 (8-inch) round cake pans coated with nonstick spray.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. Remove and let cool.
When cool, spread one layer with raspberry jam and sprinkle with half the fresh raspberries.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Dust remaining layer with sugar and garnish with remaining berries.
Serve at once or refrigerate up to 1 hour before serving.

title: 10 minute fudge
directions: Brown wheat bread makes the best grilled cheese sandwiches. White bread may be used also.

title: snow pudding with custard sauce
directions: Mix as for jello and let stand until it begins to set.
Beat whites of 3 eggs until stiff.
Then beat into gelatin.
Chill.

title: spinach quiche
directions: In medium size bowl, combine spinach, eggs, milk, onion, mushrooms, sausage and grated cheese.
Pour mixture in pie shell. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato corn souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off top third of each tomato; scoop out seeds and pulp.
Coat inside with mustard and spoon in souffle.
Top with grated cheese.
Place in buttered baking dish and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pork and beans and hot dog casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, with casserole covered, then 8 minutes uncovered.
Bacon slices may be put on top of beans before baking.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first six ingredients; stir until smooth.
Add the oats, blending well (dough will be stiff).
Cover and chill 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls; place 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Dip fork in flour; flatten cookies to 3/4 inch thickness. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool cookies on wire racks. Yields 4 dozen.

title: quickie cutlets
directions: Mix chuck, veal, salt and pepper very well.
Form into 8 patties.
Fold pieces of cheese in four; place on one of the patties, then cover with another patty.
Press the edges together so the cheese is well sealed inside.

title: ribs and beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain.
Place in boiler.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and onion.
Brown short ribs.
Place in baking dish (the beans).
Put short ribs on top.
Bake until meat is tender and beans are done.
Add water, if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom steak and gravy
directions: Combine steak, water, 1 package Food Club mushroom gravy mix, salt, pepper, oregano, parsley, and 2 teaspoons Nature's seasoning into large covered skillet (12 inches).
Cook about 2 hours.
Add water if needed.

title: fettuccine with garlic shrimp
directions: Heat oil in frying pan. Add garlic and chili.
Saute for 1 minute. Add shrimp and cook over medium-high heat until shrimp turns pink, about 3 minutes. Add basil and salt.
Cook pasta in boiling, salted water following package directions.
Drain.
Place fettuccine in heated serving bowl.
Pour shrimp and oil remaining in pan on top. Toss and serve.

title: fruit dips
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and butter until smooth; beat in Marshmallow Creme. Fold in whipped topping. Serve with fruit. Store in refrigerator. A sprinkle of cinnamon is good when using apples. Also good on toast.

title: ginger bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and add boiling water.
Stir well. Bake slowly in large pan at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Place ingredients in large mixing bowl in order.
Mix well following addition of sugar.
Mix again after adding eggs.
Final mixing after oil and juice.
Pour into loaf tins lined with waxed paper.
Make 6 small (3 x 7 x 2-inch) loaves and bake at 275° for 2 hours or 4 large (4 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch) loaves and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and spinach enchiladas
directions: Add spinach to onion.
Cook and stir until moisture evaporates.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Ricotta and broccoli.
Take 1/3 cup picante and spices. Stir and mix.
Put in tortillas and place in slightly greased dish.
Add remaining picante sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and return to oven.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine instant pie filling mix, whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla in small mixer bowl.
Beat slowly until blended, then increase speed to high until mixture is very thick, about 3 minutes.
Slice bananas into crust and top with filling.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping mix.
Refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients, adding the buttermilk to make the consistency you desire. After pouring batter on griddle, sprinkle with chopped dates, nuts, peanut butter, etc. on top before turning.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes; turn down to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: 1922 butterscotch pie recipe
directions: Cook together sugar, shortening and cream until thick and brown.
The browner it cooks, the more butterscotch taste it has. Mix milk, flour and egg yolk and stir into first mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chocolate cookies(no bake)
directions: Stir sugar, milk, cocoa and butter over heat until it boils good.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; stir to mix.
Drop onto waxed paper with spoon; let cool.

title: no bake graham squares
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers.
In a saucepan, mix together the egg, brown sugar, oleo and water. Cook until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the graham cracker crumbs, coconut, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Mix well and spread over graham crackers.
Place a layer of crackers on top.
Mix together the 1/3 stick oleo, milk, vanilla and enough confectionary sugar to make a frosting.
Frost the bars.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Combine the asparagus with soup and top with crumbled buttered crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter 9 x 15-inch pan.
Melt all in pan.
Cut stick of oleo and spread pineapple over bottom of pan (juice and all).
Put cherries and juice on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Cover mixture with nuts and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: krumkake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter well before adding flour and flavoring.
Makes a good size recipe, but can be doubled easily. Cook on krumkake iron.
When light brown, remove and roll on krumkake form.

title: biscuits
directions: Do not handle dough any more than necessary and these biscuits are wonderful.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Have powdered sugar sifted out on a large spot on kitchen counter.
Mix sugar, Karo and water in a large pan.
Cook until hard-crack (300°) on candy thermometer.
Turn heat off immediately. Add food coloring.
Add cinnamon oil.
Pour candy over powdered sugar immediately.
(Will not melt counter.)
When candy cools, break into pieces.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low-medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Blend in flour.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until light browned.
Add tomatoes, water, tomato sauce, wine, bouillon cube, sugar, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in parsley.
Use for meat, chicken dishes, eggplant, etc.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream both sugars and Crisco.
Mix in eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls after the dough has been chilled.
Press cookies with potato masher or fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk and cheese.
Sprinkle chicken with flour and seasonings, then dip into buttermilk mixture, coating both sides and using entire mixture.
Dip chicken into crumbs, turning to coat both sides.
In small nonstick skillet, heat oil; add chicken.
Cook, turning once, until done.
Serve with 12 ounces steamed vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and spices.
Form into balls or logs.
Can sprinkle with chili powder or roll in chopped parsley or nuts. Chill.
Makes 2 cheese balls.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple-nut salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve pudding with juice from crushed pineapple.
When pudding is thoroughly dissolved, add the other ingredients.
Pour into serving dish (or two 8-inch pans or one 9 x 12-inch pan).
Garnish with cherries and more walnuts, if desired.
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in a slightly buttered casserole. Melt the stick of margarine (can use microwave) and add the crumbled crackers. Mix together and sprinkle over top of the vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin apple cake
directions: Mix until creamy; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until done at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the beans and corn and put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Mix together the sour cream, cheese, onions and soup and put on top of beans.
Mix the almonds, margarine and crackers well and put on top of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Cream
the
sugar and shortening.
Add egg and pumpkin. Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: pizza fruit pie
directions: You will need a large cookie sheet with sides.

title: creamy marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows and salt.
Cook until bubbly. Boil on medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oleo, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip; add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: apple roll
directions: Chop apples and mix with brown sugar and spice.
Melt butter, sugar and water in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix flour and shortening with enough cold water to blend.
Roll out dough and spread apple mixture on dough.
Roll up and slice.
Stir butter, sugar and water.
Put apple roll slices in pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
While noodles cook, mix Ricotta, egg substitute and drained spinach together.
Place 1/2 cup sauce in bottom of 8 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish and spread to the edges.
Place 2 lasagna noodles on sauce and top with 1/2 of spinach cheese mixture.
Layer 2 slices of Mozzarella over spinach.
Repeat layers:
noodles, spinach mixture and Mozzarella.
Finish with a layer of noodles.
Pour remaining sauce over layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 90 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: "bilodi" taco pie casserole(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add taco mix, olives and tomato sauce. Separate crescent rolls; flatten and press to make a crust in a casserole dish.
Cover with Fritos.
Spoon meat mixture over Fritos.
Spread with sour cream, then sprinkle with cheese.
Top with more crushed Fritos.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
While cake is baking, mix together condensed milk and pina colada.
While cake is still warm, punch holes, with a spoon handle, every 1 to 1 1/2-inches over cake.
Drizzle milk and pina colada mixture over top, filling holes.
Repeat.
Spread whipped cream over the cake and sprinkle with coconut.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Chill.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Dip in wax and chocolate mixture made from melting and stirring together the wax and chocolate.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone, cut into chunks.
Mix together sour cream and soup, then add chicken chunks.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix crushed crackers and margarine, put over casserole then sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes just until bubbly.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and cream with Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well after each addition of milk and flour. Add salt and flavoring.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300° or in sheet cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole 3
directions: Thaw veggies first or boil for 5 minutes.
Combine all veggies in an 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt Velveeta with 1/2 stick butter until smooth (can use microwave).
Pour over veggies evenly.

title: fried cheese
directions: Cut cheese into 3/4-inch cubes.
Dip cheese cube in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Repeat twice.

title: applesauce gelatin pie
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling; add gelatin and cook until dissolved.
Mix in sugar.
Whip 1 cup very cold evaporated milk until stiff with lime or lemon juice.
Pour this slowly into gelatin mixture.
Some fruit can be folded in also, i.e., strawberry, raspberry, etc.
Put in baked shell and chill at least 1 hour.
Can be made with sugar-free substitutions also.

title: sage dressing
directions: Combine cornbread and biscuit crumbs.
Add sage and black pepper to taste.
Bring broth to a boil.
Pour into crumb mixture until it forms a ball.
Make 2-inch balls and place into baking dish. Pour broth over dressing balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: basic baking chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: canadian spareribs
directions: Arrange spareribs in a roasting pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake another 2 hours.
Serve.

title: french lace cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, salt, oats, egg, baking powder, flour, vanilla and coconut.
Batter will be runny.
Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Drop batter by tablespoon 3 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch carefully.
These burn easily.
Cool; peel off foil.
Store in an airtight container. Makes 36 cookies.

title: peas and pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add celery; cook a few minutes. Add peas; cook a few more minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook a couple of minutes.
Combine with pasta.

title: stove top beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on top of stove until well heated and cheese is melted.
Add hot dogs.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, pepper and red pepper.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cook slow and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add milk, mushroom soup, cooked chicken and cooked spaghetti. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: layered revenge dip
directions: Mix the sour cream and taco mix.
Layer all the items (except Tostitos chips) in a dish with about 1-inch sides.
Ummmm!
A hearty dip loved by all.
My family calls it, "Montezuma's Revenge."

title: old-fashion baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; boil gently for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain; save liquid.
Dice salt pork and divide.
Put half in the bottom of a pot and add whole onion.
Put beans in next and top with remaining pork.
Mix remaining ingredients with bean liquid and pour over beans.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours, adding liquid when needed.

title: josi's quick chicken breasts
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place chicken breasts on broiler pan; spread with mustard and cover with bread crumbs.
Gently turn breasts and spread with mustard and crumbs.
Broil 3 or more minutes on each side, depending on size of breasts.

title: baked chicken and vegetables
directions: Remove skin from breasts.
Place chicken, meaty sides up, in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan; sprinkle with paprika.
Place zucchini, carrots and mushrooms around and over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients; drizzle over chicken and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours.
Spread with pie filling, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until slightly thick and golden brown.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt butter, add mushrooms; sprinkle with flour, toss.
Cook over medium heat; stirring for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce, slowly stir in cream.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Season to taste.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Mash bananas in a large bowl until smooth; makes about 1 1/2 cups. Stir in oil, vanilla and salt.
Add oats, oat bran, mixed fruit and nuts, stirring well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto cookie sheets about 1 inch apart and flatten out slightly with back of a spoon.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bottom and edges are lightly browned.
Transfer to cookie wire rack.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cookies (2)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs and sugar, followed by other ingredients.	Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: Using an electric mixer, mix together the peanut butter and margarine.
Using a wooden spoon, gradually add the powdered sugar.
Sometimes it is easier to use your hands to mix the last of the sugar into the mixture.
Shape this mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip the balls into the chocolate mixture which has been melted over a double boiler.
In my family this is a traditional candy at Christmas time.

title: graham pone
directions: Mix together.
Put into greased pan and bake.
Can be served with sugar and milk or fruit.
This is also known as johnnycake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased baking dish.

title: mostaccioli pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; cool.
Pour blended mixture over pasta.
Cool overnight.

title: praline clusters
directions: Combine sugar, whipping cream and water in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (236°) using a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat with wooden spoon until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken.
Stir in pecans.
Working quickly, drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased wax paper.
Cool.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Roll
out in small balls and put them on your sweetened fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: gloria's peanut butter balls(candy)
directions: In large bowl, combine the peanut butter and pancake syrup. Mix well. Stir in the powdered sugar to form thick clay-like dough. Roll in 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper to dry while you melt the chocolate. Dip half of ball in chocolate to form "buckeyes." Or dip all the way in chocolate for a bonbon. Chill 15 minutes to set chocolate. These freeze well.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all together (use only 1 cup of nuts).
Shape into ball. Roll in remaining cup of nuts. Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Put milk and butter on stove until butter melts, then stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickens, then add vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top before baking.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: french pear pie
directions: Simmer pears until tender in small amount of water; drain. Arrange pears in shell.
Combine flour, sugar, ginger and yogurt; mix well.
Pour over pears.
Combine flour, brown sugar and nutmeg. Cut in butter to make crumbly topping.
Sprinkle over filling. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Partially melt cranberry sauce and add to jello.
Add sugar, pineapple, nuts and rind when slightly cool.
Congeal and serve.

title: apple kueshen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix (dry), butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of crumbly mixture.
Press remaining crumbly mixture in bottom of an ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Arrange apple slices on mixture in pan.
Beat sour cream and egg until blended; spread over apples.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbly mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until topping is light brown.
Cool.
Serves 16.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Grease	a
x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Steam broccoli
about 3 minutes.	Cool and press dry.
Beat eggs and milk
until
frothy.
Thoroughly
mix flour, baking powder and salt;
stir
into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese
and
onion.
Spoon into baking dish, spreading evenly. Sprinkle
with
seasoned
salt.
Bake
in a 350° oven about 35 minutes
or
until set and lightly brown.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut into bite size pieces.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
In casserole dish, combine eggs, onions, soup, Miracle Whip and broccoli.
Put cheese on top and then cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients together to form a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with vegetables and crackers.

title: banana onion salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine crackers and nuts in a greased, large shallow baking pan.
In a saucepan, bring butter, sugar and corn syrup to a boil and cool for five minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda.
Pour caramel mixture over crackers and nuts; stir well.
Bake one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper and break apart; allow to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields approximately 9 cups.

title: roast beef casserole
directions: Place in baking dish.
Season to taste.
Cook until meat is done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy nacho dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream and cream cheese.
Add desired amount picante sauce (mixture should be creamy).
Spread evenly onto serving dish.
Layer cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in buttered 7 x 11-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of first mixture.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: In a mixer, mix together; refrigerate.
Put cherries on top.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cook margarine and flour for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange first five ingredients evenly in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix balance of ingredients and spread evenly over potatoes.
Decorate top with more catsup, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound 1 cup flour in steak until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Slice mango over top.
Put carrots, tomatoes and onions over top and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: baking powder biscuits(heritage recipe)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix in shortening, using fork; add milk. Blend lightly until mixture is moistened. Turn out on floured surface; knead lightly. Roll out to about 3/4 inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place o lightly greased baking pan. Also, brush tops lightly with melted margarine or bacon grease. Bake 400 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar gradually; beat well and add sour cream.
Mix well and add eggs one at a time.
Slowly add flour, mixing thoroughly, then add vanilla.
Beat 3 or 4 minutes.
Grease and lightly flour a Bundt pan; pour in mixture and bake in a preheated 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Dust balls with confectioners sugar.
Makes a lot!
